  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Appoints Jeremiah as a Prophet to the Nations'
      title: Yahweh Appoints Jeremiah as a Prophet to the Nations
      number: 1
      content: 'The words of Jeremiah, the son of Hilkiah, among the priests who
        were in Anathoth, in the land of Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'to whom the word of Yahweh came in the days of Josiah the son of
        Amon, the king of Judah, in the thirteenth year of his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It came also in the days of Jehoiakim, the son of Josiah, the king
        of Judah, until the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah, the son of Josiah,
        the king of Judah, until the exile of Jerusalem in the fifth month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBefore I formed you in the womb I knew you, and before you
        came out from the womb I consecrated you; I appointed you as a prophet to
        the nations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord Yahweh! Look, I do not know how to speak,
        for I am a youth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Yahweh said to me, \u201CYou must not say, \u2018I am a youth,\u2019
        for to whomever I send you, you will go, and whatever I command you, you
        will speak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Do not be afraid of them, for I am with you to deliver you,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Yahweh stretched out his hand and he touched my mouth, and Yahweh
        said to me, \u201CLook, I have put my words in your mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Yahweh Confirms Jeremiah\u2019s Call"
      title: "Yahweh Confirms Jeremiah\u2019s Call"
      number: 10
      content: "See, I appoint you this day over the nations and over the kingdoms,
        to pluck up and to pull down, and to destroy and to tear down, to build and
        to plant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the word of Yahweh came to me, saying, \u201CWhat are you seeing,
        Jeremiah?\u201D And I said, \u201CI am seeing a branch of an almond tree.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Yahweh said to me, \u201CYou did well to see, for I am watching
        over my word to perform it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the word of Yahweh came to me a second time, saying, \u201CWhat
        are you seeing?\u201D And I said, \u201CI am seeing a boiling pot, and its
        face is from the face of the north.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Yahweh said to me, \u201CFrom the north disaster will be unleashed
        on all the inhabitants of the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For, look, I am calling to all the clans of the kingdoms of the north,\u201D
        declares Yahweh, \u201Cand they will come and set each one his throne at
        the entrance of the gates of Jerusalem, and against all its surrounding walls,
        and against all the cities of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I will pass my judgments on them because of all their wickedness
        in that they have forsaken me, and they made sacrifices to other gods, and
        they bowed in worship to the works of their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But you, you must gird your loins, and stand, and speak to them all
        that I command you. Do not be afraid of them, or I will shatter you before
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now look, I have made you today as a fortified city and as an iron
        pillar and a bronze wall against all the land, against the kings of Judah,
        against its princes, against its priests, and against the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And they will fight against you but they will not prevail against
        you, for I am with you,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cto deliver you.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh Remembers Israel\u2019s Faithfulness"
      title: "Yahweh Remembers Israel\u2019s Faithfulness"
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo and proclaim in the ears of Jerusalem, saying, \u2018Thus
        says Yahweh, \u201CI remember concerning you the loyal love of your childhood, 
        the love of your betrothal-time, your going after me in the desert,  in the
        land not sown. "
      comments: []
    - name: "3: The Unfaithfulness of Israel\u2019s Ancestors"
      title: "The Unfaithfulness of Israel\u2019s Ancestors"
      number: 3
      content: "Israel was holy to Yahweh, the first fruit of his produce. All those
        who ate it were held guilty; disaster came to them,\u201D declares Yahweh.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear the word of Yahweh, O house of Jacob, and all the clans of the
        house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CWhat injustice did your ancestors find in
        me that they were far from me, and they went after the vanity, and they became
        vain? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And they did not say, \u2018Where is Yahweh, the one who brought
        us up from the land of Egypt, the one who led us in the desert,  in a land
        of desert plains and gorges,  in a land of dryness and deep darkness, in
        a land that no one passes through,  and no human lives there?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I brought you to the land of the orchard, to eat its fruit, and
        its good things.  But you entered and defiled my land, and my inheritance
        you made a detestable thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Unfaithfulness of Contemporary Israel'
      title: The Unfaithfulness of Contemporary Israel
      number: 8
      content: "The priests did not say, \u2018Where is Yahweh?\u2019 and those who
        handle the law did not know me, and the shepherds have rebelled against me, 
        and the prophets prophesied by Baal, and they went after things which do
        not profit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore I again bring a lawsuit against you,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cand with your children I bring a lawsuit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For go over to the coasts of Cyprus and look, and send to Kedar and
        consider very closely, and see if there has been a thing like this: '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Has a nation exchanged gods? And they are not gods! But my people
        have exchanged their glory for that which does not profit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Be appalled, O heavens, at this, and shudder; be utterly desolate,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFor my people have committed two evils: they have forsaken
        me, the source of living water, to hew out for themselves cisterns, cracked
        cisterns that can hold no water. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Is Israel a slave? Or a slave born in a house?  Why has he become
        plunder? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The young lions have roared against him, they have raised their voices. 
        And they have made his land as horror; his cities are destroyed, without
        an inhabitant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover, people of Memphis and Tahpanhes will shave your skull.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Did you not do this to yourself, by forsaking Yahweh, your God, at
        the time of your leading in the way? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And now why do you go the way of Egypt to drink the waters of the
        Shihor? And why do you go the way of Assyria to drink the waters of the Euphrates?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Your wickedness will chastise you, and your apostasies will reprove
        you. Therefore know and see that it is evil and bitter, your forsaking of
        Yahweh, your God, and fear of me is not in you,\u201D declares the Lord,
        Yahweh of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFor from long ago you have broken your yoke, you tore to pieces
        your bonds. And you said, \u2018I will not serve!\u2019 But on every high
        hill and under every leafy tree you were lying down as a prostitute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yet I planted you as a choice vine, all of it a seed of trustworthiness.
        How then have you altered before me into something that is degenerate, the
        foreign vine? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For if you wash with natron, and you use much soap,  your guilt is
        sticking as a stain before me,\u201D declares the Lord Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CHow can you say, \u2018I have not defiled myself, I have not
        gone after the Baals?\u2019 Look at your way in the valley, know what you
        have done. You are a young she-camel, interweaving her ways. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'A wild ass accustomed to the desert,  in the desire of her soul.
        She gasps for wind in her rutting time. Who can quell her lust? All those
        who seek her will not grow weary, in her month they will find her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Restrain your foot from being barefoot, and your throat from thirst.
        But you said, \u2018It is hopeless. No! For I have loved strangers, and after
        them I will go.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'As the shame of a thief when he is caught in the act, so the house
        of Israel will be ashamed. They, their kings, their officials, and their
        priests, and their prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Those who say to the tree, \u2018You are my father,\u2019 and to
        the stone, \u2018You gave birth to me.\u2019 For they have turned their backs
        to me, and not their faces. But in the time of their trouble they say, \u2018Arise
        and save us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But where are your gods that you made for yourself? Let them arise
        if they can save you in the time of your trouble. For according to the number
        of your towns are your gods, O Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Why do you complain to me? All of you have rebelled against me,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CFor in vain I have struck your children. They accepted no discipline.
        Your sword devoured your prophets, like a ravening lion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "O generation, you see the word of Yahweh. Have I been a desert to
        Israel? Or a land of great darkness? Why do my people say, \u2018We roam
        about freely, we will not come again to you\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Can a young woman forget her ornaments? Or a bride her sashes? Yet
        my people have forgotten me days without number. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'How well you do on your way to seek love! Therefore even to the wicked
        woman you can teach your ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Also on your skirts is found the blood of the life of the innocent,
        the poor. You did not find them in the act of breaking into a house. But
        in spite of all these things, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "yet you say, \u2018But I am innocent, surely his anger has turned
        away from me.\u2019 Look, I am entering into judgment with you because of
        your saying, \u2018I have not sinned.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'How you go about so much changing your way! Also by Egypt you will
        be put to shame, just as you were put to shame by Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Also from there you will come out with your hands on your head, for
        Yahweh has rejected those in whom you trust,  and you will not prosper through
        them. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " A saying: \u2018Look, if a man divorces his wife, and she goes from
        him and she becomes another man\u2019s wife,  will he return to her again?\u2019
        Will not that land be greatly defiled? And you have prostituted yourself
        with many lovers, would you now return to me?\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CLift up your eyes at the barren heights, and see where you
        have not been ravished. Beside the roads you sat for them like an Arab in
        the desert,  and you have defiled the land with your fornication and with
        your wickedness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore rain showers have been withheld, and the spring rain has
        not come. Yet you have the forehead of a woman prostitute, you refuse to
        be ashamed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Have you not just now called to me, \u2018My father, you are the
        close friend of my youth? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Yahweh Gives Israel a Letter of Divorce'
      title: Yahweh Gives Israel a Letter of Divorce
      number: 5
      content: "Will he be angry forever?  Will he maintain it always\u2019?  Look,
        you have spoken, but you have done all the evil that you could.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Yahweh said to me in the days of Josiah, the king, \u201CHave
        you seen what apostate Israel has done? She has gone on every high hill and
        under every leafy tree and she has prostituted herself there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I thought, \u2018After her doing all these things to me she will
        return,\u2019 but she did not return. And her treacherous sister Judah saw
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I saw that for this very reason, that on account of apostate
        Israel committing adultery I divorced her and gave the letter of divorce
        to her. Yet her treacherous sister Judah was not afraid and she went and
        prostituted herself also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it was because of the frivolity of her fornication that she defiled
        the land and committed adultery with the stone and with the tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: A Call for Repentance'
      title: A Call for Repentance
      number: 10
      content: "Yet even in all this her treacherous sister Judah did not return
        to me with all her heart, but only in pretense,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Yahweh said to me, \u201CApostate Israel has proved herself
        more upright than treacherous Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Go, and proclaim these words toward the north, and say, \u2018Return,
        apostate Israel,\u2019 declares Yahweh. \u2018I will not cause my anger to
        fall on you. For I am loyal,\u2019 declares Yahweh. \u2018I will not be angry
        forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Only acknowledge your guilt, that against Yahweh your God you have
        rebelled, and have scattered your ways to the strangers under every leafy
        tree, and you have not obeyed my voice,\u2019 declares Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CReturn, apostate children,\u201D declares Yahweh. \u201CFor
        I am your master, and I will take you one from a city and two from a clan,
        and I will bring you to Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then I will give you shepherds after my own heart and they will feed
        you knowledge and insight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And it will be when you have multiplied and become fruitful in the
        land in those days,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cthey will no longer say,
        \u2018The ark of the covenant of Yahweh.\u2019 And it will not come to mind,
        nor will they remember it, nor will they miss it, nor will it be made again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "At that time they will call Jerusalem \u2018The Throne of Yahweh,\u2019
        and all the nations will be gathered to it, to the name of Yahweh, to Jerusalem,
        and they will no longer go after the stubbornness of their evil heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In those days the house of Judah will walk along with the house of
        Israel and they will come together from the land of the north to the land
        that I gave as an inheritance to your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then I thought, \u2018How I would set you among the children, and
        I would give you a land of desire, an inheritance of the glory of the hosts
        of nations.\u2019 And I thought, \u2018You would call me, \u201CMy father,\u201D
        and you would not turn back from behind me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "However, as a wife departs treacherously from her lover, so you have
        dealt treacherously with me, O house of Israel,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CA voice is heard on the barren heights, the weeping of the
        pleas for mercy of the children of Israel, because they have perverted their
        way, they have forgotten Yahweh their God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Return, O apostate children, I will heal your backsliding. \u2018Look,
        we come to you, for you are Yahweh our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Surely, an illusion comes from the hills, the turmoil on the mountains.
        Surely, in Yahweh our God is the salvation of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But the shameful thing has devoured the labor of our ancestors from
        our youth, their flocks, and their cattle, their sons and their daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Let us lie down in our shame, and let our disgrace cover us. For
        against Yahweh our God we have sinned, we and our ancestors,  from our youth
        and until this day. and we have not obeyed the voice of Yahweh our God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " If you return, O Israel,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cyou return
        to me. And if you remove your abominations from my presence,  and you do
        not wander, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and you swear, \u2018As Yahweh lives,\u2019  in truth, in justice,
        and in righteousness, then nations will be blessed by him, and in him they
        will boast.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says Yahweh to the men of Judah and to Jerusalem, \u201CBreak
        up for yourselves prepared virgin soil, and you must not sow among thornbushes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: An Invasion from the North'
      title: An Invasion from the North
      number: 4
      content: "Circumcise yourselves to Yahweh, and remove the foreskins of your
        hearts,  men of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem, lest my wrath goes forth
        like the fire and burns, and there is no one who extinguishes it,  because
        of the evil of your deeds.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Declare in Judah and proclaim in Jerusalem and say, \u201CBlow a
        horn through the land, call with a loud voice and say, \u2018Be gathered
        and let us go into the fortified cities.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Lift up a signal toward Zion, bring yourselves to safety; you must
        not remain standing, for I am bringing evil from the north, and a great destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A lion has gone up from his thicket, and a destroyer of nations has
        set out. He has gone out from his place to make your land as a horror, your
        cities will go to ruin without inhabitant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Because of this gird yourselves with sackcloth, lament and wail,
        for the burning anger of Yahweh has not turned back from us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And then on that day,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cthe heart of the
        king and the heart of the officials will be destroyed, and the priests will
        be appalled, and the prophets will be astonished.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord Yahweh, surely you have utterly deceived
        this people and Jerusalem, saying, \u2018It will be peace for you,\u2019
        while the sword reaches up to the throat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "At that time it will be said to this people and to Jerusalem, \u201CA
        hot wind from the barren heights in the desert,  in the direction of the
        daughter of my people, not to winnow and not to cleanse, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "a wind too strong for these will come for me, now also I speak judgments
        against them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Look, he comes up like the clouds, and his chariots are like the
        whirlwind, his horses are swifter than eagles, woe to us, for we are devastated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Cleanse your heart from wickedness, O Jerusalem, so that you may
        be saved. How long will your thoughts of mischief dwell in your inner part? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For a voice is declaring from Dan, and is proclaiming disaster from
        the mountain of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CReport to the nations, \u2018Here they are!\u2019 Proclaim
        against Jerusalem, \u2018Besiegers are coming from a distant land,  and they
        raise their voice against the cities of Judah.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Like watchers of a field they were against her from all around, because
        she has rebelled against me,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou obtained this for yourself because of your way and your
        deeds. This is your doom, for it is bitter, yes, it has reached up to your
        heart.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My bowels, my bowels! I writhe! The walls of my heart! My heart is
        restless within me, I cannot keep silent, for I hear in my inner self the
        sound of a horn, the alarm of war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Destruction on destruction is proclaimed, for all of the land is
        devastated. Suddenly my tents are devastated, my tent curtains in a moment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'How long must I see the banner, and hear the sound of a horn? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor my people are foolish, they have not known me. They are
        foolish children, and they do not have insight. They are skillful at doing
        evil, and they do not know how to do good.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I looked at the earth, and behold, it was wasteland and emptiness,
        and to the heavens, and they were without their light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I looked at the mountains, and behold, they were quaking, and all
        of the hills were jolted to and fro. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I looked and behold, there was no person, and all of the birds of
        the sky had fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I looked and behold, the fruitful land was a desert,  and all of
        its cities were ruined before Yahweh, before the face of his burning anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u201CAll of the land will be a desolation,
        yet I will not make a complete desolation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Because of this the earth will mourn, and the heavens above will
        become dark. Because I have spoken, I have planned, and I have not relented,
        and I will not turn back from it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From the sound of a horseman and an archer every town flees, they
        enter in the thickets and among the rocks they climb. Every town is forsaken,
        and there is no person who lives in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And you, O devastated one, what do you do, that you put on crimson,
        that you adorn yourself with ornaments of gold, that you make your eyes look
        bigger with the eye make-up? In vain you beautify yourself. Your lovers reject
        you; they seek your life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For I heard a voice like an ill woman, anxiety like a woman who bears
        her first child, the voice of the daughter of Zion. She is gasping for breath,
        she is spreading out her hands: \u201CWoe is me, for I am becoming tired
        before killers.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CRoam about through the streets of Jerusalem, and look please,
        and take note, and search at its public squares, if you can find a person
        who does justice, who seeks honesty, so that I may forgive it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And though they say, \u2018As Yahweh lives,\u2019  therefore they
        swear falsely.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O Yahweh, do not your eyes look for honesty? You have struck them,
        but they felt no pain, you have destroyed them, they refused to take discipline.
        They have hardened their faces more than rock, they have refused to turn
        back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said, \u201CThey are just simple people, they are foolish,
        for they know not the way of Yahweh, the law of their God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Let me go to the great, and let me speak with them, for they know
        the way of Yahweh, the law of their God.\u201D However, they together have
        broken the yoke, they have torn to pieces the bonds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore a lion from the forest will kill them, A wolf from the
        desert plains will devastate them. A leopard is watching their cities, everyone
        who goes out from there will be torn, because their transgressions are many,
        their apostasies are numerous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CHow can I forgive you? Your children have forsaken me, and
        they have sworn by those who are not gods. But I fed them to the full, and
        they committed adultery, and flocked to the house of a prostitute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They were well-fed lusty horses, they neighed each to the wife of
        his neighbor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Because of these things shall I not punish?\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cand on a nation who is like this, shall I not take revenge? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Go up through her vineyards and destroy, but you must not make complete
        destruction. Remove her branches, for they are not to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the house of Israel and the house of Judah have dealt utterly
        treacherously with me,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThey have denied Yahweh, and have said, \u2018Not he, for evil
        will not come on us, we will see neither sword nor famine. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the prophets are like wind, and the word is not in them.\u2019
        Thus it will be done to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh, the God of hosts, \u201CBecause you have
        spoken this word, look, I am making my words in your mouth like a fire, and
        this people wood, and it will devour them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Look, I am about to bring on you a nation from afar, O house of Israel,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. \u201CIt is an enduring nation, it is an ancient nation. 
        A nation whose language you do not know, and you cannot understand what they
        speak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their quiver is like an open tomb, all of them are warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they will eat your harvest and your food, they will eat your
        sons and your daughters, they will eat your flock and your herd, they will
        eat your vine and your fig tree, they will smash with the sword your fortified
        cities,  in which you trust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut even in those days,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201CI will
        not make you a complete destruction. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And then, when you people say, \u2018Why has Yahweh our God done
        all of these things to us?\u2019 Then you will say to them, \u2018As you
        have forsaken me and have served gods of a foreign land in your land, so
        will you serve strangers in a land that does not belong to you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CDeclare this in the house of Jacob, and proclaim it in Judah,
        saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Hear this please, O foolish and senseless people, who have
        eyes but do not see, who have ears but do not hear.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Do you not revere me?\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201CDo you not tremble
        before me?  For I have placed the sand as a boundary for the sea, as an everlasting
        limit, and it cannot pass over it, and they rise and fall loudly, but they
        cannot prevail, and its waves roar, but they cannot pass over it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But for this people is a stubborn and rebellious heart, they have
        turned aside and have gone away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they do not say in their hearts, \u2018Let us fear please Yahweh
        our God, the one who gives the autumn rain and the spring rain in its season,
        the set times of the harvest he keeps for us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your iniquities have disturbed these, and your sins have kept away
        the good from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For wicked people are found among my people, they lie in wait like
        the hiding of fowlers, they set up a trap, they catch humans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Like a cage full of birds,  so their houses are full of fraud. Therefore
        they have become great, and they have become rich. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They have grown fat, they have grown sleek, also, their evil deeds
        have no limit.  They do not judge with justice, the legal cause of the orphan,
        or allow it to succeed, and the legal case of the poor, they do not defend. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Because of these things shall I not punish?\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cand on a nation who is like this, shall I not take revenge? "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'A horrific event and something horrible has happened in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The prophets prophesy falsely,  and the priests rule by their own
        authority,  and my people love it so much. But what will you do when the
        end comes?  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Flee for safety, O children of Benjamin, from the midst of Jerusalem.
        And in Tekoa blow a horn, and on Beth-haccherem lift up a signal, for evil
        looks down from the north, and a great destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The lovely and the delicate, the daughter of Jerusalem, I will destroy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shepherds and their flocks will come against her, they will pitch
        their tents against her all around, they will pasture, each his portion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Sanctify war against her. Arise, and let us attack at noon. Woe to
        us, for the day turns, for the shadows of evening are lengthened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Arise, and let us attack by night, and let us destroy her citadel
        fortresses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus says Yahweh of hosts, \u201CCut down trees and heap up a
        siege ramp against Jerusalem. This is the city that must be punished, its
        oppression is in its midst. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As a water well keeps its water cool, so she keeps cool her wickedness.
        Violence and destruction are heard within her, sickness and wounds are continually
        before me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Be warned, O Jerusalem, lest I turn away from you in disgust, lest
        I make you a desolation, a land that is not inhabited.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CThey will thoroughly glean the remnant
        of Israel as a vine, turn back your hand over the branches like a grape-gatherer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'To whom shall I speak and admonish, that they may hear? Look, their
        ears are closed,  and they are not able to listen attentively. Look, the
        word of Yahweh is to them an object of scorn, they do not delight in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But I am full with the wrath of Yahweh, I struggle to hold it in.
        Pour it out on the children in the street, and on the assemblies of young
        men at the same time. For even husband with wife will get trapped, the old
        with him who is full of days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And their houses will be turned over to others, their fields and
        their wives together. For I will stretch out my hand against the inhabitants
        of the land,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFor from the smallest of them to the greatest of them, everyone
        makes profit for unlawful gain. And from the prophet to the priest, everyone
        practices deceit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And they have treated the wound of my people lightly, saying, \u2018Peace,
        peace,\u2019 but there is no peace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Have they acted ashamed, for they have committed a detestable thing?
        Not at all, nor were they ashamed; they did not know to feel humiliated.
        Therefore they will fall among those who fall at the time I punish them,
        they will stumble,\u201D says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CStand at the roads and look, and ask for
        the ancient paths, where the way of the good is, and walk in it, and find
        rest for your inner selves.  But they said, \u2018We will not walk in it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And I raised up watchmen over you: \u2018Listen attentively to the
        sound of a horn.\u2019 But they said, \u2018We will not listen attentively.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore hear, O nations, and know, O community, what will happen
        to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hear, O earth, look, I am about to bring disaster to this people,
        the fruit of their plans, because they have not listened attentively to my
        words, and my teaching, they have rejected it also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "What is this to me? Frankincense comes from Sheba, and the precious
        spice reed from a distant land. Your burnt offerings are not acceptable, 
        your sacrifices are not pleasing to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh: \u201CLook, I am about to put before
        this people stumbling blocks, and they will stumble against them, fathers
        and children together, neighbor and his friend will perish.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CLook, a people is coming from the land of
        the north, a great nation is woken up from the farthest part of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The bow and the short sword they grasp are cruel, and they show no
        mercy. Their sound roars like the sea, and on horses they ride, drawn up
        like a man for battle against you, O daughter of Zion.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'We have heard news of it, our hands grow slack, anxiety has grasped
        us, pain as a woman who gives birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You must not go out into the field, and you must not walk on the
        road, for the enemy has a sword,  terror is all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'O daughter of my people, gird yourself with sackcloth, and roll about
        in the ashes in mourning, a mourning ceremony as for an only child. Make
        for yourself wailing of bitterness, for suddenly the destroyer will come
        upon us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI have made you an assayer among my people, a fortification,
        so that you may know and put to the test their ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'All of them are stubborn rebels, going about talking slander. They
        are bronze and iron, they are all behaving corruptly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The bellows are burned up, lead is consumed by fire. In vain he keeps
        on refining,  but the wicked are not torn apart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "They are called rejected silver, For Yahweh has rejected them.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Proclamation at the Gate of the House of Yahweh"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Proclamation at the Gate of the House of Yahweh"
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CStand in the gate of the house of Yahweh and proclaim there
        this word, and say, \u2018Hear the word of Yahweh, all of Judah, those who
        enter through these gates to bow in worship to Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CMake your ways
        and your deeds good and let me dwell with you in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Do not trust in the deceitful words, saying, \u2018The temple of
        Yahweh, the temple of Yahweh, they are the temple of Yahweh.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For if you truly make your ways and your deeds good, if you truly
        do justice between a man and his neighbor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'you do not oppress the alien, the orphan, and the widow, you do not
        shed innocent blood in this place, and you do not go after other gods to
        your harm,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then I will let you dwell in this place, in the land that I gave
        to your ancestors forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Look, you are relying for yourselves on deceitful words without benefiting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will you steal? Will you murder? And will you commit adultery? And
        will you swear falsely? And will you make a smoke offering to the Baal? And
        will you go after other gods whom you have not known? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And then you come and you stand before me in this house, which is
        called by my name, and you say, \u2018we are safe to go on doing all of these
        detestable things.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Has this house, which is called by my name, become a cave of robbers
        in your eyes? Look, I, even I, have seen it,\u201D  declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CFor go now to my place that was in Shiloh, where I caused my
        name to dwell in the beginning, and see what I did to it because of the wickedness
        of my people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And now, because of your doing all these things,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cand I have spoken to you over and over again, and you have not listened,
        and I called you, and you have not answered, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'therefore I will do to the house that is called by my name, in which
        you are trusting, and to the place that I gave to you and to your ancestors
        what I did to Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I will cast you out of my sight just as I cast out all of your
        blood relatives, all of the offspring of Ephraim.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd you, you must not pray for this people, and you must not
        lift up for them a cry of entreaty or a prayer, and you must not plead with
        me, for I will not hear you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do you not see what they are doing in the towns of Judah and in the
        streets of Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The children are gathering wood, and the fathers are kindling the
        fire, and the women are kneading dough to make sacrificial cakes for the
        queen of heaven, and they pour out libations to other gods for the sake of
        provoking me to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Are they provoking me to anger? \u201D declares Yahweh, \u201CIs
        it not themselves they hurt, for the sake of the shame of their faces?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord Yahweh, \u201CLook, my anger and my
        wrath will be poured out on this place, on the humankind, and on the animal,
        and on the tree of the field, and on the fruit of the ground, and it will
        not be extinguished.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CAdd your burnt
        offerings to your sacrifices, and eat the flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I did not speak with your ancestors, nor did I command them in
        the day of bringing them out from the land of Egypt, concerning the matter
        of burnt offering and sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But I only commanded them this word, saying, \u2018Obey my voice,
        and I will be to you God, and you will be to me people, and you must walk
        in all of the way that I command you, so that it goes well with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yet they did not obey, and they did not incline their ear, but they
        walked in their own plans, in the stubbornness of their evil heart, and they
        became worse instead of better.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'From the day that your ancestors came out from the land of Egypt
        until this day I have sent to you all my servants the prophets, day after
        day, sending again and again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Yet they have not listened to me and they have not inclined their
        ear, but they have hardened their neck, they did more evil than their ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Valley of the Slaughter'
      title: The Valley of the Slaughter
      number: 27
      content: 'So you shall speak to them all these words, but they will not listen
        to you, and you shall call to them, but they will not answer you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall say to them, \u2018This is the nation that has
        not obeyed the voice of Yahweh their God, and they have not accepted discipline.
        The truth has perished, and it is cut off from their mouths.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Shear your hair and throw it away, and lift up a lament on the barren
        heights, for Yahweh has rejected and forsaken the generation of his wrath.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For the people  of Judah have done evil in my eyes,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201CThey have set their abominations in the house that is called
        by my name, to defile it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And they built the high place of Topheth, which is in the Valley
        of Ben Hinnom, to burn their sons and their daughters in the fire, which
        I have not commanded, and it did not come into my mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore look, days are about to come,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        it will no longer be called Topheth or the Valley of Ben Hinnom, but the
        Valley of the Slaughter, and they will bury in Topheth until there is no
        more place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the dead bodies of this people will be as food for the birds
        of the heavens, and for the animals of the earth, without anyone to scare
        them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And I will cause to disappear from the towns of Judah and from the
        streets of Jerusalem the sound of jubilation, and the sound of joy, the voice
        of the bridegroom, and the voice of the bride, for the land will become a
        site of ruins. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAt that time,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cthey shall bring
        out the bones of the kings of Judah, and the bones of its officials, and
        the bones of the priests, and the bones of the prophets, and the bones of
        the inhabitants of Judah from their graves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And they shall spread them out before the sun, and before the moon,
        and before all the host of heaven, which they have loved, and which they
        have served, and which they have gone after, and which they have inquired
        about, and to which they have bowed in worship. They shall not be gathered,
        and they shall not be buried; they will be like dung on the surface of the
        ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Yahweh Questions His People'
      title: Yahweh Questions His People
      number: 3
      content: "And death will be preferred to life by all the remaining of this
        evil clan in all the remaining places where I have driven them away,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall say to them, \u2018Thus asks Yahweh: \u201CDo
        men fall and not stand up? If one turns away does he not return? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why has this people, Jerusalem, turned away in enduring apostasy?
        They have kept hold of deceit, they have refused to return.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I have listened attentively, and I have listened. They do not speak
        honestly, there is no man who regrets his wickedness, saying, \u2018What
        have I done?\u2019 All of them are turning to their ways of running, like
        a horse plunging into battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Even the stork in heaven knows its appointed time, and the turtledove,
        and the swallow, and the song bird, they observe the time of their coming.
        But my people do not know the ordinance of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "How can you say, \u2018We are wise and the law of Yahweh is with
        us\u2019? Look, surely the lying stylus of the scribes has made it a lie. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The wise will be put to shame, they will be dismayed, and they will
        get taken. Look, they have rejected the word of Yahweh, and what is wisdom
        to them? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore I will give their wives to others, their fields to conquerors,
        because from the smallest to the greatest, all of them make profit for unlawful
        gain, from prophet to priest, all of them practice deceit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And they have treated the wound of the daughter of my people lightly,
        saying, \u2018Peace, peace,\u2019 but there is no peace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Were they ashamed, for they had committed a detestable thing? What\u2019s
        worse, they were not ashamed at all, and they did not know to feel humiliated.
        Therefore they will fall among those who fall; at the time of their punishment
        they will stumble,\u201D says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: The Nation Longs for Yahweh\u2019s Help"
      title: "The Nation Longs for Yahweh\u2019s Help"
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI will take away their harvest,\u201D declares Yahweh. \u201CThere
        are no grapes on the vine, and there are no figs on the fig tree, and the
        leaves wither, and what I gave to them passed over them.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Why are we sitting? Gather, and let us go into the fortified cities,
        and let us perish there, for Yahweh our God has caused us to perish, and
        has provided drink for us, water of poison, because we have sinned against
        Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'We hope for peace, but there is no good, for a time of healing, but
        there is terror. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CFrom Dan is heard the snorting of their horses, from the sound
        of the neighing of their stallions all the land quakes, for they come and
        devour the land, and that which fills the city, and those who live in it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For look, I am letting loose among you snakes, adders for which there
        is no incantation, and they will bite you,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CMy comfort is gone from me, sorrow is on me, my heart is sick. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Look, the sound of the cry for help of the daughter of my people
        from a distant land, \u2018Is Yahweh not in Zion? Is her king not in her?\u2019
        Why have they provoked me to anger with their images, with idols of a foreign
        land?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Yahweh\u2019s Lament"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Lament"
      number: 20
      content: 'The harvest has passed, the summer has come to an end, and we have
        not received help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CBecause of the wound of the daughter of my people I am broken
        down, I mourn, horror has seized me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Is there no balm in Gilead? Is there no healer there? Why, then,
        has the healing of the daughter of my people not been restored? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '   Oh that my head were waters,  and my eyes a fountain of tears,
        so that I might weep day and night, for the slain of the daughter of my people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Oh that I had in the desert a place of overnight lodging for travelers,
        that I may leave my people and go from them, for all of them are adulterers,
        a band of traitors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: A Nation Characterized by Deceit'
      title: A Nation Characterized by Deceit
      number: 3
      content: "And they bend their tongue like their bow, for falsehood and not
        truth is superior in the land, for they go forth from evil to evil, and they
        do not know me,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLet everyone be on your guard against his neighbor, and you
        must not trust in any brother, for everyone surely betrays, and every neighbor
        goes about with slander. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And everyone deceives his neighbor, and they do not speak the truth,
        they have taught their tongues to speak lies,  they are tired from going
        astray. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Your dwelling is in the midst of deceit, upon deceit they refuse
        to know me,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore, thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CLook, I am about to refine
        them, and I will test them, for what else can I do, because of the presence
        of the daughter of my people? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their tongue is a murderous arrow, it speaks deceit. With his mouth
        he speaks peace with his neighbor, but in his inner parts he sets up his
        ambush. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Because of these things shall I not punish them?\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201COn a nation that is like this shall I not take revenge? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the mountains I lift up weeping and wailing, and for the pastures
        of the desert a lament, because they are laid waste so that no man passes
        through. And the sounds of cattle are not heard, from the birds of heaven
        to the animals  they have fled, they are gone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I will make Jerusalem as heaps of ruins, a lair of jackals, and
        the towns of Judah I will make a desolation, without inhabitants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Nation is Judged by Yahweh'
      title: The Nation is Judged by Yahweh
      number: 12
      content: "Who is the wise man that can understand this? And to whom has the
        mouth of Yahweh spoken, so that he may declare it? Why is the land destroyed?
        It is laid waste like the desert so that no one passes through.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Yahweh said, \u201CBecause of their forsaking my law that I set
        before them, and they have not obeyed my voice, and have not walked in it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "but they went after the stubbornness of their heart, and after the
        Baals, which their ancestors taught them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CLook,
        I am feeding this people wormwood, and providing drink for them, water of
        poison, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and I will scatter them among the nations that they have not known,
        they and their ancestors, and I will send the sword after them until I bring
        them to an end.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CConsider closely, and call for the
        wailing women, so that they come, and for the skillful women, so that they
        come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And let them hasten, and let them lift up wailing over us, so that
        our eyes may melt with tears, and our eyelids may flow with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For a sound of wailing is heard from Zion, \u2018How we are devastated!
        We are very ashamed because we have left the land, because they have overthrown
        our dwelling places.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For hear, O women, the word of Yahweh, and let your ear receive the
        word of his mouth, and teach your daughters a lamentation, and each woman
        her neighbor a lament. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For death has come into our windows, it has entered into our fortresses,
        to cut off the children from the streets,  the young men from the public
        squares. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Things in Which Yahweh Delights'
      title: The Things in Which Yahweh Delights
      number: 22
      content: "Speak, \u2018thus declares Yahweh: \u201CThe dead body of the human
        will fall like dung upon the surface of the field, and like cut grain behind
        the reaper, and there is no one who gathers.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u201CThe wise man must not boast in his wisdom,
        and the warrior must not boast in his might, the wealthy man must not boast
        in his wealth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Way of the Nations'
      title: The Way of the Nations
      number: 24
      content: "But only in this must the one who boasts boast, that he has insight,
        and that he knows me, that I am Yahweh, showing loyal love, justice, and
        righteousness on the earth, for in these things I delight,\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CLook, days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand I will
        call into account all those who are circumcised in the foreskin: "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Egypt, Judah, and Edom, and the Ammonites, and Moab, and all those
        who are trimmed to the side, those who live in the desert, for all the nations
        are uncircumcised, and all the house of Israel are uncircumcised of heart.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Hear the word that Yahweh speaks to you, O house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CYou must not learn the way of the nations,
        and you must not be dismayed by the signs of the heavens, for the nations
        are dismayed by them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the statutes of the peoples are vanity, for it is a tree cut
        down from the forest, the work of the hands of a craftsman with the tool. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He decorates it with silver and gold, they strengthen it with nails
        and hammers, so that it does not stagger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They are like scarecrows in a cucumber field, they cannot speak.
        Indeed, they must be carried, for they cannot march. You must not be afraid
        of them, for they cannot do evil; furthermore, to do good is not in them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There is none like you, O Yahweh, you are great and your name is
        great in might. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who would not revere you, O king of the nations? For you it is fitting.
        For among all the wise men of the nations, and in all their kingdoms,  there
        is none like you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At the same time they are stupid and foolish, in the instruction
        of idols, it is wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Silver beaten from Tarshish is brought, and gold from Uphaz, the
        work of the craftsman and the hands of the goldsmith. Blue and purple are
        their clothing, all of them are the work of skillful people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But Yahweh is the true God, he is the living God, and an everlasting
        king.  Because of his wrath the earth quakes, and the nations cannot endure
        his anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CThus you shall say to them, \u2018Gods who did not make the
        heavens and the earth will perish from the earth and from under these heavens. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He is the maker of the earth by his power, who created the world
        by his wisdom, and by his understanding he stretched out heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he utters his voice there is a noise of water in the heavens,
        and he causes the mist to rise from the ends of the earth. He makes lightning
        for the rain, and he causes the wind to go out from his storehouses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Everyone is stupid, without knowledge,  every goldsmith is ashamed
        by his divine image, for his cast image is an illusion, and there is no breath
        in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They are vanity, a work of mockery, at the time of their punishment,
        they will perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The portion of Jacob is not like these, for he is the creator of
        everything, and Israel is the tribe of his inheritance, Yahweh of hosts is
        his name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Gather your bundle from the ground, you who live under the siege.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Nation Accepts Its Judgment'
      title: The Nation Accepts Its Judgment
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, I am about to sling out the inhabitants
        of the land at this time, and I will bring distress to them, so that they
        may feel it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Woe to me, because of my wound. My wound is incurable. But I said,
        \u201CSurely this is my sickness, and I must bear it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My tent is devastated, and all my tent cords are torn. My children
        have gone out from me, and they are not. There is no one who pitches my tent
        again, or one who puts up my tent curtains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the shepherds have become stupid, they do not seek Yahweh. Therefore
        they do not have insight, and all of their flock are scattered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Listen, news:  Look, it is coming, a great roar from the land of
        the north, to make the cities of Judah a desolation, a lair of jackals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I know, O Yahweh, that to the human is not his own way, nor to a
        person is the walking and the directing of his own step. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Chastise me, O Yahweh, but in moderation, not in your anger, lest
        you eradicate me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Pour out your wrath on the nations that do not know you, and on the
        peoples that do not call on your name, for they have devoured Jacob, they
        have devoured and consumed him, and they have caused his settlement to be
        desolate. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Broken Covenant'
      title: The Broken Covenant
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear the words of this covenant, and speak to the people of
        Judah and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u201CThe
        man is cursed who does not obey the words of this covenant, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "which I commanded your ancestors in the day of my bringing them from
        the land of Egypt, from the furnace of iron, saying, \u2018Listen to my voice
        and do according to all that I command you, so will you be my people, and
        I will be your God.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "in order to keep the oath that I swore to your ancestors, to give
        them a land flowing with milk and honey, as it is this day.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        Then I answered and said, \u201CLet it be so, O Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u201CProclaim all these words in the cities
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, saying, \u2018Hear the words of
        this covenant and do them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "for I solemnly admonished your ancestors in the day of my leading
        them out from the land of Egypt and up to this day, admonishing persistently,
        saying, \u201CObey my voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But they did not obey and they did not incline their ear. Instead
        each one walked in the stubbornness of his evil heart. Therefore, I brought
        on them all the words of this covenant which I commanded them to do, and
        they did not do it.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u201CA conspiracy is found among the people
        of Judah and among the inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They have turned back to the iniquities of their former ancestors,
        who refused to obey my words, and they have gone after other gods, to serve
        them. The house of Israel and the house of Judah have broken my covenant
        that I made with their ancestors.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh, \u201CI am about to bring on them disaster
        from which they will not be able to escape. Though they cry out to me, yet
        I will not listen to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the cities of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem will go
        and cry out to the gods to whom they are making smoke offerings, but they
        will certainly not save them in the time of their trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the number of your towns are your gods, O Judah, and the number
        of the streets of Jerusalem are the altars you have set up to the shameful
        things, to make smoke offerings to Baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore you must not pray for this people, and you must not lift
        up for them a cry of entreaty, or a prayer, for I will not listen in the
        time of their calling to me, in the time of their trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'What rights has my beloved in my house  when she has done many wicked
        things?  Can the flesh of holiness pass over you? For you engage in your
        wickedness, then you exult. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Yahweh called your name, \u2018A leafy olive tree, beautiful with
        fine fruit.\u2019  With the sound of a great storm he will set fire to it,
        and its branches will be good for nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: A Warning for the People of Anathoth'
      title: A Warning for the People of Anathoth
      number: 17
      content: "And Yahweh of hosts, the one who planted you, has spoken evil against
        you, because of the evil of the house of Israel and the house of Judah, that
        they have done to themselves, to provoke me to anger by making smoke offerings
        to Baal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Moreover, Yahweh let it be made known to me, and I knew. Then you
        showed me their deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And I was like a gentle ram-lamb that is brought to slaughter, and
        I did not know that they planned plans against me, saying, \u201CLet us destroy
        the tree with its fruit, and let us cut him off from the land of the living,
        so that his name will no longer be remembered.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But O Yahweh of hosts, who judges in righteousness, who tests the
        inmost being, and the mind,  let me see your retribution upon them, for to
        you I have revealed my legal case. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh concerning the people of Anathoth who
        seek your life, saying, \u201CYou shall not prophesy in the name of Yahweh
        or you will die by our hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CLook, I am about to punish
        them. The young men will die by the sword. Their sons and their daughters
        will die by the famine. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And a remnant will not be left for them, for I will bring disaster
        to the people of Anathoth, the year of their punishment.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      number: 1
      content: 'You will be in the right, O Yahweh, when I complain to you. Even
        so, let me speak my claims with you. Why does the way of the wicked succeed?
        All those who deal treacherously with treachery are at ease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Not only do you plant them, they take root. They grow, but also they
        produce fruit. You are near in their mouths, but far from their inmost beings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But you, O Yahweh, you know me, you see me, and you test that my
        heart is with you. Tear them apart like sheep for the slaughtering, and set
        them apart for the day of slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: The Lord\u2019s Reply"
      title: "The Lord\u2019s Reply"
      number: 4
      content: "How long will the land mourn, and the vegetation of every field dry
        up, because of the wickedness of those who live in it? The animals and the
        birds are swept away, because they have said, \u201CHe does not see our future.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf you run with foot soldiers and they have made you weary,
        then how will you compete with horses? If you have fallen in a peaceful land, 
        then how will you do in the thickets of the Jordan? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For even your relatives, and the house of your father, even they
        have dealt treacherously with you, even they call loudly after you. You must
        not trust in them, though they speak kindly to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I have forsaken my house, I have abandoned my inheritance. I have
        given the beloved one of my heart into the hand of her enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My inheritance has become to me like a lion in the forest. She has
        lifted up against me her voice; therefore I hate her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The lair of the hyena is my inheritance to me, the birds of prey
        are all around her. Go, gather all of the animals of the field, bring them
        to come and devour.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Many shepherds have destroyed my vineyard, they have trampled down
        my plot of land. They have made my pleasant field  like the desert of desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They have made it a desolation. Desolate, it mourns to me. All the
        land is made desolate, but there is no person taking it to heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Upon all the barren heights in the desert destroyers have come, for
        the sword of Yahweh devours, from one end of the land to the other end of
        the land, there is no peace for all flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They have sown wheat and they have reaped thorns. They are exhausted,
        they do not profit. And they will be ashamed of your produce, because of
        the burning anger of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says Yahweh concerning all of the evil neighbors who touch the
        inheritance that I gave as an inheritance to my people Israel: \u201CLook,
        I am about to drive them out from their land, and the house of Judah I will
        drive out from among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And then after my driving them out, I will once again have compassion
        on them, and I will bring them back, each one to his inheritance, and each
        one to his land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And then, if they diligently learn the ways of my people, to swear
        by my name, \u2018as Yahweh lives,\u2019 even as they taught my people to
        swear by Baal, then they will live in the midst of my people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if they do not listen, then I will completely uproot and destroy
        that nation.\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Linen Loincloth'
      title: The Linen Loincloth
      number: 1
      content: "Thus Yahweh said to me: \u201CGo and buy for yourself a loincloth
        of linen and put it on your loins, but you must not place it in water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought the loincloth according to the word of Yahweh and I put
        it on my loins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the word of Yahweh came to me a second time, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTake the loincloth that you bought, that is on your loins,
        and stand up, go to the Euphrates and hide it there in the cleft of the rock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So I went and hid it by the Euphrates just as Yahweh had commanded
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And then, after a long time, then Yahweh said to me, \u201CStand
        up, go to the Euphrates and take from there the loincloth that I commanded
        you to hide there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then I went to the Euphrates and I dug, and I took the loincloth
        from the place where I had hidden it, and look, the loincloth was ruined;
        it was not good for anything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And then the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018So I will ruin the pride of Judah and
        the great pride of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This evil people, who refuse to listen to my words, who go in the
        stubbornness of their hearts, and have gone after other gods, to serve them,
        and to bow in worship to them, let them be like this loincloth which is not
        good for anything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For as the loincloth clings to the loins of a person, so I caused
        to cling to me all the house of Israel and all the house of Judah,\u2019
        declares Yahweh, \u2018to be for me a people, and a name, and a praise, and
        a glory, but they would not listen.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore, you shall say to them this word, \u2018Thus says
        Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u201CEvery jar must be filled with wine.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019
        And they will say to you, \u2018Do we not certainly know that every jar should
        be filled with wine?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says Yahweh: \u201CLook, I
        am about to fill all the inhabitants of this land, and the kings who sit
        on David\u2019s throne, and the priests, and the prophets, and all the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem with drunkenness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I will smash them, each one against his brother, and the fathers
        and the sons together,\u201D declares Yahweh. \u201CI will not have compassion,
        and I will not take pity, and I will not show compassion from destroying
        them.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Listen, and pay attention, you must not be haughty, for Yahweh has
        spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Give glory to Yahweh your God before he brings darkness, and before
        your feet stumble on the mountains at twilight. And you will hope for light,
        but he makes it as gloom, he makes it as thick darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: A Message for the King and the Queen Mother'
      title: A Message for the King and the Queen Mother
      number: 17
      content: 'But if you will not listen to it, my inner self will weep in secret
        places, because of the presence of your pride. And my eyes will weep bitterly,
        and they will melt in tears, because the flock of Yahweh has been taken captive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CSay to the king and to the queen mother, \u2018Take a lower
        seat,  for your beautiful crown has come down from your head.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The towns of the Negev are shut up, and there is no one who opens
        them.  All of Judah is deported; it is deported in completeness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Lift up your eyes and see those coming from the north. Where is the
        flock that was given to you, your magnificent flock?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "What will you say when he sets over you\u2014 and you have taught
        them\u2014allies as head over you? Will not labor pains take hold of you,
        like a woman giving birth? "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And if you say in your heart, \u2018Why have these things happened
        to me?\u2019 Because of the greatness of your iniquity your skirts are uncovered;
        your heels have endured violence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Can a Cushite change his skin, or a leopard his spots? Then you also
        will be able to do good, who are accustomed to doing evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And I will scatter them like stubble scattered by the wind of the
        desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "This is your lot, the portion of your measure from me,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201Cbecause you have forgotten me, and you have trusted in the
        lie. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So in turn I will bare your skirts over your face, and your shame
        will become visible. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Your adulteries, and your neighings, the shameful behavior of your
        fornications on the hills in the countryside, I have seen your abominations.
        Woe to you, O Jerusalem! How long will you continue to be unclean?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Severe Drought'
      title: The Severe Drought
      number: 1
      content: 'That which came as the word of Yahweh to Jeremiah concerning the
        matter of the severe drought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CJudah mourns, and her gates languish, they are in mourning
        on the ground, and the cry of lament of Jerusalem goes up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And their nobles send their servants for water. They come to the
        pits, they find no water. They return with their vessels empty.  They are
        ashamed, and they are confounded, and they cover their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because of the ground, which is cracked because there was no rain
        on the ground. The farmers are ashamed, they cover their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For even the doe in the field gives birth and forsakes her young, 
        because there is no green growth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And wild asses stand on the barren heights, they gasp for breath
        like the jackals. Their eyes fail because there is no vegetation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Although our iniquities testify against us, O Yahweh, act for the
        sake of your name. Yes, our apostasies are many; we have sinned against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You are the hope of Israel, its savior in time of distress. Why should
        you be like an alien in the land, or like a traveler who spreads out his
        tent  to spend the night? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Why should you be like a confused man, like a warrior who is not
        able to help? Yet you are in our midst, O Yahweh, and your name is called
        upon us. You must not leave us! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Lying Prophets'
      title: Lying Prophets
      number: 10
      content: "Thus says Yahweh concerning this people: \u201CThey have loved so
        much to wander, they have not spared their feet. Therefore Yahweh is not
        favorable to them, now he will remember their iniquity and punish their sins.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Yahweh said to me, \u201CYou must not pray for this people, for
        their happiness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Although they fast, I am not listening to their cry of entreaty.
        And although they present burnt offering and grain offering, I am not favorable
        to them. But by the sword, and by the famine, and by the plague, I am about
        to destroy them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord Yahweh, look, the prophets are saying
        to them, \u2018You will not see the sword, and famine will not be yours,
        but reliable peace I will give to you in this place.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Yahweh said to me, \u201CThe prophets are prophesying lies in
        my name. I have not sent them, and I have not commanded them, and I have
        not spoken to them. They are prophesying to you a lying vision, and a divination,
        worthless, and the deceitfulness of their minds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh concerning the prophets who prophecy in
        my name though I have not sent them, yet they are saying, \u201CSword and
        famine will not be in this land.\u201D&nbsp;\u201CBy the sword and by the
        famine those prophets will perish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Nation Hopes in Yahweh'
      title: The Nation Hopes in Yahweh
      number: 16
      content: 'And the people to whom they are prophesying will be cast out into
        the streets of Jerusalem because of the famine and the sword. And there will
        be no one who buries them, their wives, or their sons, or their daughters.
        And I will pour out on them their wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall say to them this word, \u2018Let my eyes melt
        with tears night and day, and let them not cease, for with a great wound
        the virgin daughter of my people is broken, with a very incurable wound. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If I go out into the field, then look, those slain by the sword.
        And if I enter the city, then look, the sickness of the famine. For both
        prophet and priest wander around through the land, they do not know what
        is going on.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Have you completely rejected Judah? Or has your soul loathed Zion?
        Why have you struck us so that there is no healing for us? We hope for peace,
        but there is no good, and for a time of healing, but look, there is terror. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'We know, O Yahweh, our wickedness, the iniquity of our ancestors, 
        for we have sinned against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You must not spurn us for the sake of your name, you must not dishonor
        your glorious throne.  Remember us!  You must not break your covenant with
        us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Are there any among the idols of the nation who cause rain to pour?
        Or can the heavens give showers? Is it not you, O Yahweh our God? Therefore,
        we hope in you, for you do all these things. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Four Types of Calamity'
      title: Four Types of Calamity
      number: 1
      content: "Then Yahweh said to me, \u201CEven if Moses and Samuel stood before
        me, my heart would not be to this people. Send them away from my sight, and
        let them go out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And then if they say to you, \u2018Where shall we go?\u2019 Then
        you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CThose who are destined
        for the plague, to the plague, and those who are destined for the sword,
        to the sword, and those who are destined for the famine, to the famine, and
        those who are destined for the captivity, to the captivity.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAnd I will summon over them four types of calamity,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201Cthe sword to kill, and the dogs to drag away, and the birds
        of the air and the wild animals of the earth to devour and to destroy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will make them a terror to all of the kingdoms of the earth
        because of Manasseh, the son of Hezekiah, the king of Judah, because of what
        he did in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor who will have compassion on you, O Jerusalem, or who will
        show sympathy to you, or who will turn aside to ask about your welfare?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You have forsaken me,\u201D declares Yahweh. \u201CYou go backward,
        so I have stretched my hand against you, and I have destroyed you. I am tired
        of becoming remorseful. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I have winnowed them with a winnowing fork in the gates of the
        land. I am bereaved. I have destroyed my people. They did not turn back from
        their ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their widows will be more numerous before me than the sand of the
        seas. I have brought to them, against the mothers of young men,  a destroyer
        at noon. I will suddenly drop on her anguish and horror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jeremiah\u2019s Lament and Yahweh\u2019s Response"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Lament and Yahweh\u2019s Response"
      number: 9
      content: "She who gave birth to seven has withered away. She gasps her breath.
        Her sun set while still day. She has been put to shame and disgraced. And
        the remainder of them I will give to the sword before their enemies,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Woe to me, O my mother, that you gave birth to me, a man of contention
        and quarreling to the whole land.  I have not lent out and I have not borrowed. 
        All of them are cursing me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Yahweh said, \u201CSurely I will set you free to be good for you,
        surely I will cause the enemy to intercede with you in a time of trouble,
        and in a time of distress. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Can anyone break iron, iron from the north, or bronze? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will give your wealth and your treasures as plunder without price,
        even because of all your sins, and throughout all your territories. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I will make you serve your enemies in a land that you do not
        know, for a fire will kindle in my anger. Upon you it will be kindled.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You who know, O Yahweh, remember me, and attend to me, and take revenge
        for me against my persecutors in your forbearance.  You must take me away.
        Know that I am carrying disgrace because of you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Your words were found and I ate them, and your words became to me
        as jubilation, even as the joy of my heart, for your name is called on me,
        O Yahweh God of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I sat not in the assembly of jokers, nor did I exult. Because of
        the presence of your hand I sat alone, for you filled me with indignation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Why is my pain endless, and my wound incurable? It refuses to become
        healed. Truly you are to me like a deceitful brook, waters that are not trustworthy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh, \u201CIf you turn back, then I will take
        you back. You will stand before me.  And if you utter what is precious and
        not what is worthless, you will be as my mouth. They will turn back to you,
        and you will not turn back to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And I will make you to this people a wall of fortified bronze, and
        they will fight against you, but they will not prevail over you, for I am
        with you, to save you, and to deliver you,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd I will deliver you from the hand of the wicked, and I will
        redeem you from the hand of the tyrant.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah is Commanded Not to Marry'
      title: Jeremiah is Commanded Not to Marry
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CYou shall not take for yourself a wife, there shall not be
        for you sons and daughters in this place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For thus says Yahweh concerning the sons and concerning the daughters
        born in this place, and concerning their mothers who gave birth to them,
        and concerning their fathers who fathered them in this land: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThey will die by diseases, they will not be mourned, and they
        will not be buried. They will be as dung on the face of the earth. And they
        will perish by the sword and they will perish by the famine. And their dead
        bodies will become food for the birds of the air, and for the wild animals
        of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u201CYou must not enter the house of the funeral
        meal, and you must not go to lament, and you must not show sympathy for them,
        for I have taken away my peace from this people,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cthe
        loyal love and the compassion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Both the great and small will die in this land. They will not be
        buried, and they will not mourn for them, and no one will cut himself with
        a blade, and no one will shave himself for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they will not break bread for the mourning ceremony for them,
        to comfort him because of the dead. And they will not give drink to them,
        the cup of desolation, for their fathers, or for their mothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And you shall not enter the house of the banquet, to sit with them,
        to eat and drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CLook, I am
        about to cause to disappear from this place, before your eyes and in your
        days, the voice of jubilation, and the voice of joy, and the voice of the
        bridegroom, and the voice of the bride. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And then when you tell this people all these words and they ask you,
        \u2018Why has Yahweh pronounced against us all this great evil, and what
        is our iniquity, and what is our sin that we have sinned against Yahweh our
        God?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then you shall say to them, \u2018Because your ancestors have forsaken
        me,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018and they have gone after other gods, and
        they have served them, and they have bowed down in worship to them, and they
        have forsaken me, and they have not kept my laws. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you have behaved badly more than your ancestors, and look, you
        are going each one after the stubbornness of his evil heart, without listening
        to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: The Nation\u2019s Return to the Land"
      title: "The Nation\u2019s Return to the Land"
      number: 13
      content: 'So I will throw you from this land to the land that you have not
        known, you or your ancestors, and there you will serve other gods day and
        night, for I will not show you favor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore look, days are coming,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018and
        it will no longer be said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, who led up the Israelites
        from the land of Egypt,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but only \u201CAs Yahweh lives, who led up the Israelites from the
        land of the north, and from all the lands where he had driven them,\u201D
        for I will bring them back to their ground that I gave to their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Look, I am sending for many fishermen,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018and
        they will fish them out, and afterward I will send for many hunters, and
        they will hunt them from every mountain, and from every hill, and from the
        clefts of the cliffs. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For my eyes are on all their ways, they are not hidden from before
        me, and their iniquity is not concealed from before my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I will first doubly repay their iniquity and their sin because
        of their profaning my land with the dead bodies of their abhorrences, and
        with their abominations they have filled up my inheritance.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "O Yahweh, my strength, and my stronghold, and my refuge in the day
        of distress, to you the nations will come from the ends of the earth, and
        they will say, \u201COur ancestors have inherited only lies,  vanity, and
        there is no profit in them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Can a human make for himself gods? Yet they are not gods!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CTherefore look, I am about to let them know, this time I am
        going to let them know my power and my might, and they will know that my
        name is Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sin of Judah'
      title: The Sin of Judah
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CThe sin of Judah is written with an iron stylus, with a point
        of diamond it is engraved on the tablet of their heart, and on the horns
        of their altars. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As the remembering of their children, so is the remembering of their
        altars and their poles of Asherah worship beside the leafy trees on the high
        hills. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O my mountain in the open country, I will give your wealth, all your
        treasures, for spoil, your high places, because of your sin, throughout all
        your territories. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The One Who Trusts in Humankind Contrasted With the One Who Trusts
        in Yahweh'
      title: The One Who Trusts in Humankind Contrasted With the One Who Trusts in
        Yahweh
      number: 4
      content: "And you will let go your hand from your inheritance  that I gave
        to you, and I will make you serve your enemies in the land that you do not
        know, for you kindled a fire in my anger, until eternity it will be kindled.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u201CCursed is the person who trusts in humankind
        and makes flesh his strength,  and turns aside his heart from Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he will be like a juniper in the wilderness,  and he will not
        see when good comes, and he will dwell in the parched places in the desert, 
        in a land of salt flats, where no one lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Blessed be the person who trusts in Yahweh, and Yahweh is his trust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For he will be like a tree planted by water, and to the stream it
        sends its roots, and it will not fear when heat comes, and its leaves will
        be luxuriant, and in the year of drought it will not be anxious, and it will
        not cease from the bearing of fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The heart is deceitful more than anything else, and it is disastrous.
        Who can understand it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I, Yahweh, examine the mind,  I test the heart,  and give to each
        one according to his way, according to the fruit of his deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Fountain of Living Water'
      title: The Fountain of Living Water
      number: 11
      content: "Like a partridge that hatches eggs it did not lay is one who amasses
        wealth without justice. In the middle of his days it will leave him, and
        at his end he will prove to be a fool.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A lofty throne of glory from the beginning is the place of our sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O Yahweh, the hope of Israel, all those who forsake you will be put
        to shame, and those who turn aside from you in the earth will be recorded,
        for they have forsaken the fountain of living water, Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Heal me, O Yahweh, and I will be healed, save me, and I will be saved,
        for you are my praise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Look, they are saying to me, \u201CWhere is the word of Yahweh? Please
        let it come.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But I, I have not run away from being a shepherd who follows you, 
        and I have not desired the disastrous day. You, you know the pronouncement
        of my lips, it was before your face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You must not become to me a terror, you are my refuge in the day
        of disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Sabbath Day'
      title: The Sabbath Day
      number: 18
      content: 'Let my persecutors be put to shame, but as for me, do not let me
        be put to shame. Let them be dismayed, but as for me, do not let me be dismayed.
        Bring on them the day of disaster, and with double destruction, destroy them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Thus said Yahweh to me, \u201CGo, and you must stand in the People\u2019s
        Gate through which the kings of Judah enter, and through which they go out,
        and in all the gates of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And you must say to them, \u2018Hear the word of Yahweh, kings of
        Judah, and all Judah, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem who enter through
        these gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u201CBe on your guard for the sake of yourselves,
        that you must not carry a burden on the day of the Sabbath, and you must
        not bring it through the gates of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you must not carry a burden from your houses on the day of the
        Sabbath, and you must not do any work. But you must declare holy the day
        of Sabbath, just as I commanded your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Yet they did not listen, and they did not incline their ear, and
        they hardened their neck so as to not hear, nor to receive discipline. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd it will happen, if you carefully listen to me,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201Cto bring no burden through the gates of this city on the day
        of the Sabbath, but to declare holy the day of Sabbath, not to do on it any
        work, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then kings and officials who sit on the throne of David will enter
        through the gates of this city riding in chariots and on horses, they, and
        their officials, the people of Judah, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and
        this city will be inhabited forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And they will come from the towns of Judah, and from all around Jerusalem,
        and from the land of Benjamin, and from the Shephelah, and from the hill
        country, and from the Negev, bringing burnt offerings, and sacrifices, and
        grain offerings, and frankincense, and bringing thank offerings to the house
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But if you do not listen to me, to declare holy the day of the Sabbath,
        and to not carry a burden and enter through the gates of Jerusalem on the
        day of the Sabbath, then I will kindle a fire in its gates, and it will devour
        the palaces of Jerusalem, and it will not be quenched.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Potter and the Clay'
      title: The Potter and the Clay
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CStand up and go down to the house of the potter, and there
        I will let you hear my words.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I went down to the house of the potter and look, there he was
        doing work at the potter\u2019s wheels. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the vessel that he was making with the clay was spoiled in the
        hand of the potter, so he made again another vessel, as it was right in the
        eyes of the potter to make. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CLike this potter, am I not able to do to you, O house of Israel?\u201D
        declares Yahweh. \u201CLook, like the clay in the hand of the potter, so
        are you in my hand, O house of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'One moment I speak concerning a nation or concerning a kingdom, to
        uproot, and to tear down, and to destroy it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if that nation turns back from its evil that I have threatened
        against it, then I will relent concerning the disaster that I planned to
        do to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the next moment I speak concerning a nation or concerning a kingdom,
        to build, and to plant it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But if it does evil in my sight, to not listen to my voice, then
        I will relent concerning the good that I said I would do to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CSo now then, say, please, to the people of Judah and to the
        inhabitants of Jerusalem, saying, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, I am
        preparing evil against you, and I am planning a plan against you. Please
        turn back, each one from his evil way, and walk rightly in your ways and
        your deeds.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But they will say, \u2018It is hopeless, for we will go after our
        own plans, and each one of us will act according to the stubbornness of his
        evil heart.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says Yahweh, \u2018Please ask among the nations,
        \u201CWho has heard the like of this?\u201D  The virgin of Israel has done
        something very horrible. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Does the snow of Lebanon leave from the crags of Sirion? Or are the
        cold waters flowing from distant mountains dried up? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But my people have forgotten me. They make smoke offerings to the
        idols,  and they caused them to stumble in their ways, the ancient ways,
        to go into bypaths, not one that is built up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'To make their land a horror, an object of whistling for eternity.
        All who pass by it will be appalled, and he will shake his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Jeremiah\u2019s Imprecatory Prayer"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Imprecatory Prayer"
      number: 17
      content: "Like the wind from the east I will scatter them before the enemy.
        I will show them my back and not my face in the day of their disaster.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they said, \u201CCome and let us plan plans against Jeremiah,
        for instruction will not be lost from the priest, nor advice from the wise
        man, nor the word from the prophet. Come and let us bring charges against
        him, and let us not listen attentively to any of his words.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Listen attentively to me, O Yahweh, and listen to the voice of my
        opponents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Should good be repaid in place of evil? Yet they have dug a pit for
        me. Remember my standing before you to speak good for them, to avert your
        wrath from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore give their children to the famine, and hand them over to
        the power of the sword, and let their wives be bereaved and widows, and let
        their men be killed by death, their young men struck dead by the sword in
        the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Let a cry for help be heard from their houses when you suddenly bring
        upon them the raiding band, for they have dug a pit to catch me, and they
        have fixed secretly a trap for my feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But you, O Yahweh, you know all their plans of assassination against
        me.  You must not make atonement for their iniquity, and you must not cause
        their sin to be blotted out from before you.  But let them be overthrown
        before you.  Deal with them in the time of your anger. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Valley of the Slaughter'
      title: The Valley of the Slaughter
      number: 1
      content: "Thus said Yahweh, \u201CGo and buy a potter\u2019s earthenware jar,
        and take some of the elders of the people, and some of the leaders of the
        priests, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and go out to the Valley of Ben Hinnom, which is at the entrance
        of the Gate of the Potsherd, and proclaim there the words that I speak to
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And you shall say, \u2018Hear the word of Yahweh, O kings of Judah
        and inhabitants of Jerusalem. Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel:
        \u201CLook, I am about to bring disaster upon this place so that everyone
        who hears it, his ears will ring. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because they have forsaken me, and they have defaced this place,
        and they have made smoke offerings in it to other gods whom they have not
        known, they, nor their ancestors, nor the kings of Judah, and they have filled
        up this place with the blood of the innocent, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and they have built the high places of Baal, to burn their children
        in the fire, burnt offerings to Baal, which I commanded not, and I ordered
        not, and it did not come to my mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CTherefore look, days are about to come,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cwhen this place will no longer be called Topheth or the Valley of Ben
        Hinnom, but the Valley of the Slaughter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will lay waste the plans of Judah and Jerusalem in this place,
        and I will bring them to ruin by the sword before their enemies, and by the
        hand of those who seek their life, and I will give their dead bodies as food
        to the birds of heaven and to the animals of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I will make this city a horror, and an object of hissing, everyone
        who passes by it will be appalled, and will hiss because of all its wounds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I will cause them to eat the flesh of their sons, and the flesh
        of their daughters, and each one will eat the flesh of his neighbor in the
        siege and in the distress which their enemies and those who seek their life
        inflict on them.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThen you shall break the jar before the eyes of the men who
        go with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CSo
        I will break this people and this city as one breaks the vessel of the potter,
        so that it is not able to be repaired again. And in Topheth they will bury
        until there is no room to bury.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Thus will I do to this place,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand to
        its inhabitants, to make this city like Topheth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the houses of Jerusalem and the houses of the kings of Judah
        will be unclean like the place of Topheth, all the houses where they made
        smoke offerings upon their roofs to all the host of heaven, and where they
        poured out libations to other gods.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Jeremiah came from Topheth, where Yahweh had sent him to prophesy,
        and he stood in the courtyard of the house of Yahweh and said to all the
        people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Look, I
        am about to bring to this city and upon all its towns all the disaster that
        I have pronounced against it, because they have hardened their neck to not
        hear my words.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message for Pashhur'
      title: A Message for Pashhur
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Pashhur, the son of Immer, the priest who was officer in charge
        in the temple of Yahweh, heard Jeremiah prophesying these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Pashhur struck Jeremiah the prophet and put him in the stocks
        that were in the upper Gate of Benjamin, which was by the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And then on the next day, when Pashhur brought Jeremiah out from
        the stocks, Jeremiah said to him, \u201CYahweh will not call your name Pashhur,
        but Terror From All Around. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u2018Look, I am making you a terror to yourself
        and to all your friends, and they will fall by the sword of their enemies,
        and your eyes will be seeing it. And all Judah I will give into the hand
        of the king of Babylon, and he will deport them to Babylon, and he will strike
        them with the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I will give all the wealth of this city, and all its acquisitions,
        and all its precious items, and all of the treasures of the kings of Judah
        I will give into the hand of their enemies, and they will plunder them, and
        they will seize them, and they will bring them to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Jeremiah\u2019s Lament"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Lament"
      number: 6
      content: "And you, Pashhur, and all those who live in your house will go into
        captivity, and you will go to Babylon, and there you will die, and there
        you will be buried, you, and all your friends to whom you have prophesied
        falsely.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have persuaded me, O Yahweh, and I was persuaded. You have overpowered
        me, and you have prevailed. I have become a laughingstock all day long. Everyone
        is mocking me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For as often as I speak, I must cry out violence and destruction.
        I must shout, for the word of Yahweh has become for me a disgrace and derision
        all day long. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But if I say, \u201CI will not mention him and I will no longer speak
        in his name,\u201D then it becomes in my heart like a fire burning, locked
        up in my bones, and I struggle to contain it,  and I am not able. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For I hear the rumor of many, \u201CTerror is from all around, denounce
        him,  yes, let us denounce him!\u201D All my close friends are watchers of
        my stumbling, saying, \u201Cperhaps he can be persuaded, and we can prevail
        over him, and we can take our revenge on him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Yahweh is with me like a powerful warrior. Therefore my persecutors
        will stumble and will not prevail. They will be very ashamed, for they will
        not achieve success. Their everlasting insult will not be forgotten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yet, O Yahweh of hosts, who tests the righteous, who sees the heart
        and the mind,  let me see your retribution upon them, for to you I have revealed
        my legal case. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Sing to Yahweh, praise Yahweh, for he has delivered the life of the
        poor from the hand of evildoers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Cursed be the day on which I was born, let not the day on which my
        mother gave birth to me be blessed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Cursed be the man who brought the news to my father, saying, \u201CA
        child is born to you, a son!\u201D and he made him very glad. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And let that man be like the cities that Yahweh demolished without
        regret, and let him hear a cry for help in the morning, and an alarm at the
        time of noon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Because he did not kill me in the womb, so that my mother would have
        been for me my grave, and her womb would be pregnant forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Why did I come out from the womb, to see toil, and sorrow, and to
        end my days in shame?  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message for Zedekiah'
      title: A Message for Zedekiah
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh when King Zedekiah sent
        to him Pashhur, the son of Malchiah, and Zephaniah, the son of Maaseiah,
        the priest, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CPlease inquire of Yahweh on behalf of us, for Nebuchadnezzar
        the king of Babylon is fighting against us. Perhaps Yahweh will do with us
        according to all his miraculous acts, so that he may go up from against us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to them, \u201CThus you shall say to Zedekiah: "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u201CLook, I am about
        to turn back the weapons of war that are in your hands, with which you are
        fighting against them, the king of Babylon and the Chaldeans who are laying
        siege to you from outside the wall, and I will gather them into the center
        of this city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I myself will fight against you with outstretched hand, and with
        strong arm, and in anger, and in fury, and in great wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I will strike the inhabitants of this city, both humankind and
        animal; by a great plague they will die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Way of Life and the Way of Death'
      title: The Way of Life and the Way of Death
      number: 7
      content: "And afterward,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201CI will give Zedekiah,
        the king of Judah, and his servants, and the people, and those who remain
        in this city from the plague, from the sword, and from the famine, into the
        hand of Nebuchadnezzar, the king of Babylon, and into the hand of their enemies,
        and into the hand of those who seek their lives, and he will strike them
        with the edge of the sword. He will not take pity on them, and he will not
        have compassion, nor will he show compassion.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd to this people you shall say, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook,
        I am setting before you the way of life and the way of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who stays in this city will die by the sword, or by the famine,
        or by the plague. And he who goes out and goes over to the Chaldeans who
        are laying siege to you will live, and his life will be to him as booty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: A Series of Messages for the House of the King of Judah'
      title: A Series of Messages for the House of the King of Judah
      number: 10
      content: "For I have set my face against this city for evil and not for good,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. It will be given into the hand of the king of Babylon, and
        he will burn it with fire.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAnd to the house of the king of Judah, \u2018Hear the word
        of Yahweh, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O house of David, thus says Yahweh, \u201CExecute judgment in the
        morning, justice, and deliver the one who has been seized from the hand of
        the oppressor, lest my wrath goes forth like the fire and it burns, and there
        is no one who quenches it  because of the evil of your deeds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Look, I am against you, O inhabitants of the valley, O rock of the
        plain,\u201D declares Yahweh; \u201Cyou who say, \u2018Who can descend against
        us, or who can enter into our hiding place?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I will punish you according to the fruit of your deeds,\u201D
        declares Yahweh, \u201CAnd I will kindle a fire in its forest, and it will
        devour all its surroundings.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " Thus says Yahweh: \u201CGo down to the house of the king of Judah
        and you must speak this word there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And you must say, \u2018Hear the word of Yahweh, O king of Judah,
        who sits on the throne of David, you, and your servants, and your people
        who enter through these gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u201CAct with justice and righteousness, and deliver
        the one who has been seized from the hand of the oppressor. And you must
        not oppress the immigrant, the orphan, and the widow. And you must not shed
        innocent blood in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And if you indeed obey this word, then kings who sit for David on
        his throne will enter through the gates of this house, riding in chariots
        and on horses, he, and his servants, and his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if you do not obey these words, I swear by myself,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201Cthat this house will become a site of ruins.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus says Yahweh concerning the house of the king of Judah, \u201CYou
        are like Gilead to me, like the head of the Lebanon. Surely I will make you
        a desert,  like cities that are not inhabited. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will consecrate against you destroyers, everyone with his weapons,
        and they will cut down your choicest cedars,  and cast them on the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And many nations will pass by this city and they will say each one
        to his neighbor, \u2018Why has Yahweh done in this manner to this great city?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they will answer, \u2018Because they abandoned the covenant
        of Yahweh their God, and bowed down in worship to other gods, and served
        them.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You must not weep for the dead person, and you must not show sympathy
        for him. Weep bitterly for the one who goes away, for he will not return,
        or see the land of his birth again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For thus says Yahweh concerning Shallum, the son of Josiah, the king
        of Judah, who reigned as king in place of Josiah his father, who went out
        from this place: \u201CHe will not return here again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But in the place where they have deported him, there he will die,
        and he will not see this land again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Woe to the one who builds his house without righteousness, and his
        upper rooms without justice. His fellow countryman, he works for nothing,
        and he does not give to him his wages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Who says \u2018I will build for myself a spacious house with large
        upper rooms,\u2019 and he cuts windows for it, and it is paneled with cedar,
        and he paints it with vermilion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Do you reign as king because you are competing in cedar? Did not
        your father eat and drink, and he did justice and righteousness, then it
        was well with him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He judged the legal cause of the needy and the poor, and then it
        was well. Is that not what it means to know me?\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut there is nothing in your eyes and your heart except your
        unlawful gain, and on shedding the blood of the innocent, and on committing
        oppression and extortion.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh concerning Jehoiakim, the son of Josiah,
        the king of Judah: \u201CThey will not lament for him, \u2018Alas, my brother,\u2019
        or \u2018Alas, sister.\u2019 They will not lament for him, \u2018Alas, lord,\u2019
        or \u2018alas, his majesty.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He will be buried with the burial of a donkey. He will be dragged
        away and thrown outside the gates of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Go up to Lebanon and cry out, and in Bashan lift up your voice, and
        cry out from Abarim, for all your lovers are shattered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I spoke to you in the times you were secure,  and you said, \u2018I
        will not listen!\u2019 This was your way from your youth, for you have not
        obeyed my voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All your shepherds will shepherd the wind, and your lovers will go
        into captivity. Yes, then you will be ashamed and humiliated because of all
        your wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Inhabitants of Lebanon, nestled among the cedars, how you will groan
        when labor pains come to you, fear and pain as the woman who gives birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Csurely if Coniah, the
        son of Jehoiakim, the king of Judah, were the seal on my right hand, surely
        from there I would wrench you off. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And I would give you into the hand of those who seek your life, and
        into the hand of those from whom you are frightened by their presence, and
        into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar, the king of Babylon, and into the hand of
        the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And I will throw you and your mother who gave birth to you to another
        country where you were not born, and there you will die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'As for the land to which they are longing to return, they will not
        return. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Is this man Coniah a despised, shattered vessel? Or a vessel in which
        there is no delight? Why are he and his offspring thrown far, and cast away
        to the land that they do not know?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'O land, land, land, hear the word of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CRecord this man as childless, a man who will
        not succeed in his days, for no man from his offspring will succeed him, 
        sitting on the throne of David and ruling again in Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to the Evil Shepherds'
      title: Woe to the Evil Shepherds
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWoe to the shepherds who destroy and scatter the flock of my
        pasture,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel concerning the shepherds
        who shepherd my people, \u201CYou yourselves have scattered my flock, and
        you have driven them away, and you do not attend to them. Look, I will punish
        you for the evil of your deeds,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CThen I myself will gather together the remnant of my flock
        from all the lands where I have driven them, and I will bring them back to
        their grazing place, and they will be fruitful, and they will become numerous. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Righteous Branch'
      title: The Righteous Branch
      number: 4
      content: "And I will raise up over them shepherds, and they will shepherd them,
        and they will no longer fear, and they will not be dismayed, and they will
        not be missing,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CLook, days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cwhen I
        will raise up for David a righteous branch, and he will reign as king, and
        he will achieve success, and he will do justice and righteousness in the
        land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In his days Judah will be saved, and Israel will dwell in safety, 
        and this is his name by which he will be called: \u2018Yahweh is our righteousness.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CTherefore look, days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cwhen
        they will no longer say, \u2018As Yahweh lives, who led up the Israelites
        from the land of Egypt,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Unfaithful Prophets'
      title: The Unfaithful Prophets
      number: 8
      content: "but \u2018As Yahweh lives, who led up, and who brought the offspring
        of the house of Israel from the land of the north and from all the lands
        where he had driven them.\u2019 Then they will live in their land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Concerning the prophets: My heart is broken in my midst. All my bones
        tremble. I have become like a drunken man, even like a man over whom wine
        has passed, because of Yahweh, and because of his holy words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the land is full of adulterers; for the land mourns because of
        a curse. The pastures of the desert are dry, and their evil has been their
        way of running, and their power is not right. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CFor both prophet as well as priest are godless, even in my
        temple I have found their wickedness,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore their way will be to them like the slippery places,
        they will be pushed in the darkness, and they will fall into it, for I will
        bring disaster on them in the year of their punishment,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CNow in the prophets of Samaria I saw a disgusting thing. They
        prophesied by Baal and they caused my people Israel to err. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And in the prophets of Jerusalem I have seen something horrible.
        They commit adultery, and they walk in lies,  and they make strong the hands
        of evildoers, so that they have not turned back each from his wickedness.
        All of them have become to me like Sodom, and its inhabitants like Gomorrah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh concerning the prophets, \u201CLook, I
        am going to let them eat wormwood and I will give them water of poison to
        drink, for from the prophets of Jerusalem went out ungodliness to all the
        land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts, \u201CYou must not listen to the words
        of the prophets who prophesy to you. They are deluding you with visions of
        their mind,  They do not speak from the mouth of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They are continually saying to those who disregard the word of Yahweh,
        \u2018Peace it will be to you,\u2019 and to each one who walks in the stubbornness
        of his heart they say, \u2018Calamity will not come upon you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For who has stood in the council of Yahweh, that he has seen and
        heard his word? Who has listened attentively to his word and heard it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Look, the storm of Yahweh has gone forth in wrath, even a whirling
        tempest. It will whirl upon the head of the wicked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The anger of Yahweh will not turn back until his doing and until
        his keeping the plans of his mind.  In latter days you will look closely
        at it with understanding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I have not sent the prophets, yet they ran. I have not spoken to
        them, yet they prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But if they had stood in my council, then they would have proclaimed
        my words to my people, and they would have caused them to turn from their
        evil way, and from the evil of their deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Am I a God from near,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand not a God
        from far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Or can a person hide himself in secret places and I cannot see him?\u201D
        declares Yahweh. \u201CDo I not fill up the heaven and the earth?\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI have heard what the prophets who prophesy lies have said
        in my name, saying, \u2018I have dreamed! I have dreamed!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'How long will this be in the hearts of the prophets who prophesy
        lies, even the prophets of the deceitfulness of their hearts,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'who plan to make my people forget my name by their dreams that they
        tell each one to his neighbor, just as their ancestors forgot my name through
        Baal? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The prophet who has with him a dream, let him tell the dream. But
        the prophet who has my word with him, let him speak my word faithfully. What
        is straw compared to wheat?\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIs not my word like fire?\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        like a blacksmith\u2019s hammer that breaks a rock into pieces? "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CTherefore look, I am against the prophets,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cwho steal my words each one from his neighbor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Look, I am against the prophets,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cwho
        take their tongues and declare as prophets, \u2018Yahweh declares.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Look, I am against those who prophesy dreams of lies,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201Cand tell them, and they caused my people to err through their
        lies, and in their recklessness, when I myself have not sent them nor commanded
        them, so they profit not this people at all,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CNow when this people, or a prophet, or a priest, ask you, saying,
        \u2018What is the burden of Yahweh?\u2019 then you shall say to them, \u2018You
        are the burden, and I will forsake you,\u2019&nbsp;\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CAnd the prophet, and the priest, and the people who say, \u2018The
        burden of Yahweh,\u2019 I will punish that man and his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Thus you shall say, each one to his neighbor and each one to his
        brother: \u2018What has Yahweh answered?\u2019 or, \u2018What has Yahweh
        spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'But you shall not mention the burden of Yahweh, for the burden is
        to each one his word, and so you twist the words of the living God, Yahweh
        of hosts, our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus you shall say to that prophet, \u2018What has Yahweh answered
        you?\u2019 or, \u2018What has Yahweh spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But if you say, \u2018The burden of Yahweh,\u2019 therefore thus
        says Yahweh, \u2018because of your saying these words, \u201CThe burden of
        Yahweh,\u201D then I will send to you, saying, \u201CYou shall not say, \u2018The
        burden of Yahweh.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Therefore look, here I am, and I will surely lift you up and forsake
        you and the city that I gave to you and to your ancestors from my presence, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "and I will bring upon you an everlasting disgrace and an everlasting
        shame that will not be forgotten.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Two Baskets of Figs'
      title: Two Baskets of Figs
      number: 1
      content: "Yahweh showed me, and look, there were two baskets of figs placed
        before the temple of Yahweh\u2014after Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon
        had deported Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, the king of Judah, with the officials
        of Judah, and the craftsmen, and the smiths, from Jerusalem and had brought
        them to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The one basket had very good figs, like early figs, and the other
        basket had very bad figs that could not be eaten because of their bad quality. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Yahweh asked me, \u201CWhat are you seeing, Jeremiah?\u201D And
        I said, \u201CFigs\u2014the good figs, very good, and the bad figs, very
        bad, that cannot be eaten because of their bad quality.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of Yahweh came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, \u2018Like these good
        figs, so I will regard as good the exiles of Judah whom I have sent away
        from this place to the land of the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I will set my eyes on them for good, and I will bring them back
        to this land. And I will build them and not annihilate them, and I will plant
        them and not uproot them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will give to them a heart to know me, that I am Yahweh, and
        they will be my people, and I will be their God, for they will return to
        me with the whole of their heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But like the bad figs that cannot be eaten because of their bad quality\u2014for
        thus says Yahweh\u2014so I will treat Zedekiah the king of Judah, and his
        officials, and the remnant of Jerusalem who remain in this land, and those
        who live in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will make them as a terror, an evil to all the kingdoms of
        the earth, as a disgrace and a proverb, as a taunt and a curse, in all the
        places where I will drive them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I will send among them the sword, the famine, and the plague,
        until they perish from the land that I gave to them and their ancestors.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Seventy Years of Servitude'
      title: Seventy Years of Servitude
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of Judah
        in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, the king of Judah, that
        was the first year of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'which Jeremiah the prophet spoke to all the people of Judah and to
        all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CFrom the thirteenth year of Josiah, the son of Amon, the king
        of Judah, even up to this day, these twenty-three years the word of Yahweh
        has come to me, and I have spoken to you over and over again, but you have
        not listened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And though Yahweh has sent all his servants the prophets to you over
        and over again you have not listened, and you have not inclined your ear
        to hear, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "saying, \u2018Turn back please, each one from his evil way, and from
        the evil of your deeds, and live on the land that Yahweh has given to you
        and to your ancestors from a long time back and until forever, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and you must not go after other gods to serve them, and to bow in
        worship to them, and you must not provoke me to anger with the work of your
        hands, then I will not do something bad to you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Yet you have not listened to me,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018so
        that you have provoked me to anger with the work of your hands for your own
        harm.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh of hosts, \u2018Because you have not obeyed
        my words, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "look, I am going to send and take all the clans of the north,\u2019
        declares Yahweh, \u2018and I will send to Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon,
        my servant, and I will bring them against this land, and against its inhabitants,
        and against all these nations all around, and I will destroy them, and I
        will make them a horror, and an object of hissing, and everlasting ruins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I will exterminate from them the sound of jubilation, and the
        sound of joy, the voice of the bridegroom, and the voice of the bride, the
        sound of the millstones, and the light of the lamp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Cup of Wrath'
      title: The Cup of Wrath
      number: 11
      content: 'And all this land will become a site of ruins, a desolation, and
        these nations will serve the king of Babylon seventy years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And then when the seventy years are fulfilled, I will punish the
        king of Babylon and that nation,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018for their iniquity,
        and the land of the Chaldeans, and I will make it an everlasting waste.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I will bring upon that land all my words that I have spoken against
        it, everything that is written in this scroll which Jeremiah prophesied against
        all the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For many nations and great kings will let them work, even them, and
        I will repay them according to their deeds, and according to the work of
        their hands.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus said Yahweh, the God of Israel, to me, \u201CTake this cup
        of the wine of wrath from my hand, and you must give it to all the nations
        to whom I am sending you to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And they will drink, and they will stagger, and they will act like
        madmen because of the presence of the sword that I am sending among them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So I took the cup from the hand of Yahweh and I gave it to all the
        nations to whom Yahweh sent me to drink: '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jerusalem and the towns of Judah, and its kings, and its officials,
        to make them a site of ruins, a horror, an object of hissing, and a curse,
        as it is this day; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pharaoh, the king of Egypt, and his servants, and his officials,
        and all his people; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and all the other people; and all the kings of the land of Uz; and
        all the kings of the land of the Philistines\u2014Ashkelon, and Gaza, and
        Ekron, and the remnant of Ashdod; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Edom, and Moab, and the Ammonites;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and all the kings of Tyre, and all the kings of Sidon, and the kings
        of the coastland that is across the sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and Dedan, and Tema, and Buz, and all those who are trimmed to the
        side; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and all the kings of Arabia, and all the kings of the other people
        who dwell in the desert;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and all the kings of Zimri, and all the kings of Elam, and all the
        kings of Media; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and all the kings of the north, near and far, each one to his brother,
        and all the kingdoms of the world that are on the face of the earth; and
        the king of Sheshach, he will drink after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says Yahweh of hosts,
        the God of Israel, \u201CDrink and become drunk, and vomit, and fall, and
        you must not rise because of the presence of the sword that I am sending
        among you.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And it will happen, if they refuse to take the cup from your hand
        to drink, then you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says Yahweh of hosts, \u201CYou
        must certainly drink! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For look, on the city that is called by my name I am beginning to
        inflict harm, and you indeed, will you go unpunished? You will not go unpunished,
        for I am summoning a sword against all the inhabitants of the earth,\u201D
        declares Yahweh of hosts.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And you yourself shall prophesy against them all these words, and
        you shall say to them: \u2018Yahweh will roar from on high, and from his
        holy dwelling place he will give his voice. He will roar mightily against
        his settlement, a jubilant shout like those who tread grapes, he will answer
        against all the inhabitants of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The rage of battle will resound to the end of the earth, for there
        is a lawsuit of Yahweh against the nations. He is entering into judgment
        with all wicked flesh, he will give them to the sword,\u2019 declares Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts, \u201CLook, disaster is going out from
        nation to nation, and a great tempest is stirred up from the farthest parts
        of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the slain ones of Yahweh will be on that day from one end of
        the earth to the other end of the earth, and they will not be mourned, and
        they will not be gathered, and they will not be buried. They will become
        like dung on the surface of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Wail, you shepherds, and cry out. And roll about in mourning in the
        dust, O leaders of the flock. For your days of slaughter and your dispersions
        have arrived, and you will fall like a vessel of desire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And flight will perish from the shepherds, and escape from the leaders
        of the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'A sound, the cry of distress of the shepherds and the wailing of
        the leaders of the flock, for Yahweh is despoiling their pasture. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the peaceful settlements are devastated because of the burning
        anger of Yahweh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "He has left his den like a lion, for their land has become a horror,
        because of the anger of the oppressors, and because of his burning anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Escapes Death'
      title: Jeremiah Escapes Death
      number: 1
      content: 'At the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, the
        king of Judah, this word came from Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Stand in the courtyard of the house
        of Yahweh, and you must speak to all the cities of Judah that come to bow
        in worship in the house of Yahweh all the words that I command you to speak
        to them. You must not omit a word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Perhaps they will listen and turn back each from his evil way, and
        I will relent of the disaster that I am planning to do to them because of
        their evil deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you shall say to them, \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018If you will
        not listen to me, to walk in my law that I have set before you,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'to listen to the words of my servants the prophets whom I have sent
        to you, over and over again, though you have not listened, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "then I will make this house like Shiloh, and this city I will make
        a curse for all the nations of the earth.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the priests and the prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah
        speaking these words in the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And then as Jeremiah finished speaking all that Yahweh had commanded
        him to speak to all the people, then the priests and the prophets and all
        the people laid hold of him, saying, \u201CYou will die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Why have you prophesied in the name of Yahweh, saying, \u2018This
        house will be like Shiloh, and this city will be in ruins, without inhabitant\u2019?\u201D
        And all the people gathered around Jeremiah in the temple of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When the officials of Judah heard these things, they came up from
        the house of the king to the temple of Yahweh, and they sat in the entrance
        of the New Gate of Yahweh\u2019s temple. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the priests and the prophets said to the officials and to all
        the people, saying, \u201CThis man deserves the death sentence, because he
        has prophesied against this city as that which you have heard with your ears.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to all the officials and to all the people, saying,
        \u201CYahweh sent me to prophesy against this house and against this city
        all the words that you have heard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now therefore amend your ways and your deeds, and obey the voice
        of Yahweh your God, and Yahweh will relent of the disaster that he has spoken
        over you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But as for me, look, I am in your hand, do to me what is good and
        right in your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Only you must certainly know that if you put me to death, you will
        bring on yourselves innocent blood, and on this city and on its inhabitants,
        for truly Yahweh sent me to you to speak all these words in your ears.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the officials and all the people said to the priests and to
        the prophets, \u201CThis man does not deserve a sentence of death, for in
        the name of Yahweh our God, he has spoken to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then men from the elders of the land arose and said to all the assembly
        of the people, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CMicah the Morashtite was prophesying in the days of Hezekiah,
        the king of Judah, and he said to all the people of Judah, saying:  \u2018Thus
        says Yahweh of hosts, \u201CZion will be plowed, and Jerusalem will become
        a heap of ruins, and the mountain of the temple as high places of wood.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Did Hezekiah, the king of Judah, and all Judah actually put him to
        death? Was he not in fear of Yahweh? And he entreated the face of Yahweh,
        and Yahweh relented of the disaster that he had spoken against them. But
        we are about to do great disaster to ourselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Indeed, there also was a man prophesying in the name of Yahweh, Uriah,
        the son of Shemaiah, from Kiriath-Jearim, and he prophesied against this
        city and against this land like all the words of Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when King Jehoiakim, and all his warriors, and all the officials
        heard his words, then the king sought to put him to death. But Uriah heard,
        and he was afraid, and he fled and went to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then King Jehoiakim sent men to Egypt. Elnathan, the son of Achbor,
        and men with him went to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they brought out Uriah from Egypt and they brought him to King
        Jehoiakim, and he struck him down with the sword, and he threw his dead body
        into the burial sites of the sons of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'However, the hand of Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah,
        so that he was not given into the hand of the people to put him to death. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Uses Fetters and Yokes to Illustrate His Message of Submission'
      title: Jeremiah Uses Fetters and Yokes to Illustrate His Message of Submission
      number: 1
      content: "In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim, the son of Josiah, the
        king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "thus said Yahweh to me\u2014\u201CMake for yourself fetters and yokes
        and put them on your neck, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and send them to the king of Edom, and to the king of Moab, and to
        the king of the Ammonites, and to the king of Tyre, and to the king of Sidon
        in the hand of the envoys who have come to Jerusalem, to Zedekiah, the king
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you must command them for their masters, saying, \u2018Thus says
        Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, this you shall say to your masters: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI have made the earth with humankind and animals that are on
        the face of the earth by my great power and by my outstretched arm, and I
        give it to whomever is right in my eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now I myself have given all these lands into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        the king of Babylon, my servant, and also the animals of the field I have
        given to him to serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And all the nations will serve him, and his son, and his grandson,
        until the coming of the time of his own land. Then many nations and great
        kings will let him work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut it will be that the nation or kingdom that will not serve
        him, Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, and that will not put his neck under
        the yoke of the king of Babylon, I will punish that nation with the sword,
        and with the famine, and with the plague,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cuntil
        I have destroyed it with my hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And you, you must not listen to your prophets, and to your diviners,
        and to your dreamers, and to your interpreters of signs, and to your sorcerers
        who are saying, \u2018You will not serve the king of Babylon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For they are prophesying to you a lie, so that you will be removed
        from your land, and I will drive you away, and you will perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the nation that will bring its neck under the yoke of the king
        of Babylon and will serve him, yet will I leave it on its land,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201Cand they will till it, and they will live in it.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And I spoke words like these to Zedekiah, the king of Judah, saying,
        \u201CBring your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon, and serve him
        and his people, and live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Why should you die\u2014you and your people\u2014by the sword, by
        the famine, and by the plague, as Yahweh has spoken concerning the nation
        that will not serve the king of Babylon? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And you must not listen to the words of the prophets who are speaking
        to you, saying, \u2018You must not serve the king of Babylon,\u2019 for they
        are prophesying a lie to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Vessels of the Temple'
      title: The Vessels of the Temple
      number: 15
      content: "For I have not sent them,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cbut they are
        prophesying in my name falsely, so that I will drive them away. And you will
        perish\u2014you and the prophets who are prophesying to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then I spoke to the priests and to all this people, saying, \u201CThus
        says Yahweh, \u2018You must not listen to the words of your prophets who
        are prophesying to you, saying, \u201CLook, the vessels of the house of Yahweh
        are about to be quickly brought back from Babylon\u201D, for they are prophesying
        a lie to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And you must not listen to them; serve the king of Babylon and live.
        Why should this city become a site of ruins? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if they are prophets, and if there is with them the word of Yahweh,
        let them please plead with Yahweh of hosts, that the vessels that are left
        over in the temple of Yahweh, and the house of the king of Judah, and in
        Jerusalem, must not go to Babylon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For thus says Yahweh of hosts concerning the pillars, and concerning
        the sea, and concerning the stands, and concerning the rest of the vessels
        that are left in this city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'which Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, did not take when he deported
        Jeconiah, the son of Jehoiakim, the king of Judah, from Jerusalem to Babylon,
        along with all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning the
        vessels that are left in the house of Yahweh, and in the house of the king
        of Judah, and in Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018They will be brought to Babylon, and there they will stay until
        the day of my attending to them,\u2019 declares Yahweh. \u2018Then I will
        bring them up and restore them to this place.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hananiah, the False Prophet'
      title: Hananiah, the False Prophet
      number: 1
      content: 'And it was in that same year, at the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah,
        the king of Judah, in the fourth year, in the fifth month, that Hananiah,
        the son of Azzur, the prophet who was from Gibeon, said to me in the house
        of Yahweh before the eyes of the priests and all the people, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, saying, \u2018I
        have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Within two years I will bring back to this place all the vessels
        of the house of Yahweh which Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon took away
        from this place and brought to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, the king of Judah, and all the
        exiles from Judah who went to Babylon, I will bring back to this place,\u2019
        declares Yahweh, \u2018For I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Jeremiah the prophet said to Hananiah the prophet before the
        eyes of the priests and before the eyes of all the people who were standing
        in the house of Yahweh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and Jeremiah the prophet said, \u201CAmen! May Yahweh do so; may
        Yahweh fulfill your words that you have prophesied, to bring back the vessels
        of the house of Yahweh and all the exiles from Babylon to this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nevertheless listen please to this word that I am speaking in your
        hearing and in the hearing of all the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The prophets who were before me and before you from ancient times
        prophesied against many countries and against great kingdoms of war, and
        of disaster, and of plague. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The prophet who prophesies peace, at the coming of the word of the
        prophet, will become known as the prophet that Yahweh has truly sent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Hananiah the prophet took the yoke from the neck of Jeremiah
        the prophet and broke it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Hananiah said before the eyes of all the people, saying, \u201CThus
        says Yahweh, \u2018This is how I will break the yoke of Nebuchadnezzar the
        king of Babylon, within two years, from the neck of all the nations.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        And Jeremiah the prophet went on his way. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah after Hananiah the prophet
        broke the yoke from the neck of Jeremiah the prophet, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo, and you must say to Hananiah, saying, \u2018Thus says Yahweh,
        \u201CYou have broken yoke bars of wood, but you have made in place of them
        yoke bars of iron.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CI have put
        a yoke of iron on the neck of all these nations, to serve Nebuchadnezzar,
        the king of Babylon, and they will serve him, and I have even given the animals
        of the open field to him.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Jeremiah the prophet said to Hananiah the prophet, \u201CPlease
        listen, Hananiah, Yahweh has not sent you, and you have made this people
        trust in a lie. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh, \u2018Look, I am going to send you from
        the face of the earth. This year you will die because you have spoken rebellion
        against Yahweh.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Hananiah the prophet died in that same year in the seventh month. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Letter to the Exiles in Babylon"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Letter to the Exiles in Babylon"
      number: 1
      content: 'And these are the words of the letter that Jeremiah the prophet sent
        from Jerusalem to the remainder of the exiles, and to the priests, and to
        the prophets, and to all the people whom Nebuchadnezzar had deported from
        Jerusalem to Babylon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'after the going out of Jeconiah the king, and the queen mother, and
        the court officials, the leaders of Judah and Jerusalem, and the artisans,
        and the smiths from Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'by the hand of Elasah, the son of Shaphan, and Gemariah, the son
        of Hilkiah, whom Zedekiah, the king of Judah, sent to Nebuchadnezzar, the
        king of Babylon, to Babylon, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, to all the exiles
        whom I have deported from Jerusalem to Babylon, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Build houses and live in them, and plant gardens and eat their
        fruit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Take wives and father sons and daughters, and take for your sons
        wives, and give your daughters to men that they may bear sons and daughters,
        and multiply there, and you must not be few. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And seek the prosperity of the city where I have deported you, and
        pray on behalf of it to Yahweh, for in its prosperity you will have prosperity.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Do not let
        your prophets who are in your midst, and your diviners, deceive you, and
        you must not listen to your dreams that you are causing them to dream. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For they are prophesying falsely to you in my name; I have not sent
        them,\u2019 declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u2018As soon as the time has passed, seventy
        years for Babylon, I will attend to you, and I will fulfill my good word
        to you, to bring you back to this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I know the plans that I am planning concerning you,\u2019 declares
        Yahweh, \u2018plans for prosperity and not for harm, to give to you a future
        and a hope. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then when you call me, and you come and pray to me, then I will listen
        to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When you search for me, then you will find me, if you seek me with
        all your heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I will let myself be found by you,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018and
        I will restore your fortunes, and I will gather you from all the nations
        and from all the places to which I have driven you,\u2019 declares Yahweh,
        \u2018and I will bring you back to the place from which I deported you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Because you have said, \u2018Yahweh has raised up prophets for us
        in Babylon\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "for thus says Yahweh concerning the king who sits on the throne of
        David and concerning all the people who live in this city, your fellow kinsmen
        who did not go with you into the exile\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "thus says Yahweh of hosts, \u2018Look, I am going to send among them
        the sword, the famine, and the plague, and I will make them like rotten figs
        that cannot be eaten because of their bad quality. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And I will pursue them with the sword, with the famine, and with
        the plague, and I will make them a terror to all the kingdoms of the earth,
        a curse, and a horror, and an object of hissing, and a disgrace among all
        the nations to which I have driven them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "because they did not listen to my words,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018when
        I sent to them my servants the prophets, sending over and over again, and
        they would not listen,\u2019 declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And you, hear the word of Yahweh, all you exiles whom I sent away
        from Jerusalem to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning Ahab, the
        son of Kolaiah, and concerning Zedekiah, the son of Maaseiah, who are prophesying
        to you in my name a lie, \u2018Look, I am going to give them into the hand
        of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, and he will strike them before your
        eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And a curse will be taken up because of them by all the exiles of
        Judah who are in Babylon, saying, \u201CMay Yahweh make you like Zedekiah
        and like Ahab, whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Shemaiah\u2019s Letter to Zephaniah the Priest"
      title: "Shemaiah\u2019s Letter to Zephaniah the Priest"
      number: 23
      content: "because they have done a disgraceful thing in Israel, and they have
        committed adultery with the wives of their neighbors, and they have spoken
        words in my name, lies that I have not commanded them, and I am he who knows,
        and I am a witness,\u2019 declares Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And to Shemaiah the Nehelamite you shall say, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, saying, \u2018Because
        you yourself sent a letter in your name to all the people who are in Jerusalem,
        and to Zephaniah, the son of Maaseiah, the priest, and to all the priests,
        saying,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CYahweh made you priest instead of Jehoiada the priest, so that
        there are overseers in the house of Yahweh over any mad man who exhibits
        the behavior of a prophet, and you must put him into the stocks and into
        the neck iron, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and so then why have you not rebuked Jeremiah the Anathothite who
        exhibits the behavior of a prophet for you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Because he has sent to us in Babylon, saying, \u2018It will be a
        long time, build houses and live in them, and plant gardens and eat their
        fruit.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "29: Jeremiah\u2019s Response to Shemaiah\u2019s Letter"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Response to Shemaiah\u2019s Letter"
      number: 29
      content: 'And Zephaniah the priest read this letter in the hearing of Jeremiah
        the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CSend to all the exiles, saying, \u2018Thus says Yahweh concerning
        Shemaiah the Nehelamite: \u201CBecause Shemaiah prophesied to you, though
        I have not sent him, and he has made you trust in a lie,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "therefore thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, I am going to punish Shemaiah
        the Nehelamite and his offspring. There will not be for him a man who lives
        in the midst of this people, and he will not see the good that I am going
        to do to my people,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201CFor he has spoken rebellion
        against Yahweh.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel and Judah Will Be Delivered from Their Distress'
      title: Israel and Judah Will Be Delivered from Their Distress
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, saying, \u2018Write for
        yourself all the words that I have spoken to you in a scroll. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For look, days are coming,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018when I will
        restore the fortunes of my people Israel and Judah,\u2019 says Yahweh, \u2018and
        I will bring them back to the land that I gave to their ancestors and they
        will take possession of it.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now these are the words that Yahweh spoke concerning Israel and concerning
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor thus says Yahweh: \u2018We have heard a sound of trembling,
        terror, and there is no peace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ask please and see whether a male can bear a child. Why do I see
        every strong man with his hands on his loins like a woman giving birth? And
        why are all their faces changed to paleness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Alas! For that day is great, there is none like it.  And it is a
        time of distress for Jacob, yet from it he will be delivered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And it will happen on that day,\u2019 declares Yahweh of hosts, \u2018I
        will break his yoke from your neck and your bonds I will tear to pieces.
        And strangers will no longer let him work as a slave. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But they will serve Yahweh their God, and David their king, whom
        I will raise up for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But you must not fear, my servant Jacob,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018and
        you must not be dismayed, Israel, for look, I am going to save you from far,
        and your offspring from the land of their captivity. And Jacob will return,
        and he will be at rest, and he will be at ease, and there will be no one
        who makes him afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I am with you,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018to save you. For
        I will make a complete destruction of all the nations to which I scattered
        you, but you I will not make a complete destruction. And I will chastise
        you to the measure, and I will not leave you entirely unpunished.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u2018Your injury is incurable, your wound
        is overcome by sickness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There is no one who pleads your cause, for your boil there is no
        healing for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'All your lovers have forgotten you, they do not care for you. I have
        struck you with the blow of an enemy, the punishment of the cruel, because
        of the greatness of your guilt, your sins are numerous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Why do you cry because of your wound? Your pain is incurable. Because
        of the greatness of your guilt\u2014your sins are vast\u2014 I have done
        these things to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore all those who devour you will be devoured, and all your
        foes, all of them will go into captivity, and those who plunder you will
        be as plunder, and all those who plunder you I will make as plunder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For I will present healing to you, and I will heal you of your wounds,\u2019
        declares Yahweh. \u2018Because they have called you an outcast, saying, \u201CIt
        is Zion, there is no one who cares for her.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u2018Look, I will restore the fortunes of the
        tents of Jacob, and I will have compassion on his dwellings, and the city
        will be rebuilt upon its mound, and the citadel fortress will stand on its
        rightful site. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And thanksgiving and the sound of merrymakers will come out from
        them, and I will make them numerous, and they will not be few. And I will
        make them honored, and they will not be lowly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And their children will be as of old, and their community will be
        established before me.  And I will punish all their oppressors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And their noble will be from them, and their ruler will come out
        from their midst. And I will bring him near and he will approach me. For
        who is he that would pledge his heart to approach me?\u2019 declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018And you will be to me a people, and I will be to you God.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Look, the storm of Yahweh! Wrath has gone forth, a whirling tempest.
        It will whirl upon the head of the wicked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The burning anger of Yahweh will not turn back until his doing, and
        until his accomplishing the plans of his mind.  In the last of the days you
        will understand it. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CAt that time,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201CI will be the God
        of all the clans of Israel, and they will be to me a people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CThe people of the survivors of the sword
        found grace in the desert;  Israel going to find their rest.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "From afar Yahweh appeared to me, saying, \u201CI have loved you with
        an everlasting love. Therefore I have drawn you with loyal love. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will again build you, and you will be built, O virgin Israel. You
        will again adorn yourself with your tambourines, and you will go forth in
        the dancing in a ring of the merrymakers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You will again plant vineyards on the mountains of Samaria. The planters
        will plant, and they will enjoy it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For there will be a day when watchmen will call in the hill country
        of Ephraim, \u2018Stand up, and let us go up to Zion, to Yahweh our God.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u201CSing for joy for Jacob with gladness,
        and shout out for the head of the nations. Proclaim, praise, and say, \u2018Save,
        O Yahweh, your people, the remnant of Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Look, I am going to bring them from the land of the north, and I
        will gather them from the remotest part of the earth. Among them the blind,
        and the lame, those who are pregnant, and those who give birth, together,
        a great assembly, they will return here. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "With weeping they will come, and with pleas for mercy I will bring
        them; I will let them walk by streams of water in a straight path. They will
        not stumble in it, for I have become to Israel a father, and Ephraim, he
        is my firstborn.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Hear the word of Yahweh, O nations, and declare in the coastlands
        from afar, and say, \u201CThe scatterer of Israel will gather him, and he
        will keep him as a shepherd his flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For Yahweh has ransomed Jacob, and he has redeemed him from the hand
        of the person stronger than he. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they will come, and they will sing for joy on the height of Zion,
        and they will be radiant over the goodness of Yahweh, over the grain, and
        over the wine, and over the olive oil, and over the young ones of the flock,
        and over the cattle. And their life will become like a well-watered garden,
        and they will never languish again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThen the young woman will rejoice in the dancing in a ring,
        and the young men and the old men together. And I will turn their mourning
        to jubilation, and I will comfort them, and I will gladden them from their
        sorrow. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I will saturate the appetite of the priests with fatness, and
        my people will be satisfied with my goodness,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u201CA voice is heard in Ramah, lamentation, the
        weeping of bitterness. Rachel is weeping for her children; she refuses to
        be comforted because of her children, for they are no more.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CRestrain your voice from weeping, and your
        eyes from tears, for there is a reward for your work,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cand they will return from the land of the enemy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And there is hope for your future,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        your children will return to their territory. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Indeed I heard Ephraim pitying themselves, \u2018You disciplined
        me, and I was disciplined, like a calf that is not trained. Bring me back
        and let me return, for you are Yahweh my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For after my turning back I repented, and after coming to understand
        I struck my thigh. I was ashamed and also humiliated, because I bore the
        disgrace of my youth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Is Ephraim my dear son, or the child of my delight? For as often
        as I have earnestly spoken against him, I still remember him. Therefore my
        bowels are turbulent for him, surely I will have compassion on him,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CSet up for yourself road markers, make for yourself signposts,
        set your mind to the main road, the road by which you went. Return, O virgin
        of Israel, return to these your cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "How long will you waver, O unfaithful daughter? For Yahweh has created
        a new thing on the earth, a woman, she shelters a man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CThey will again
        say these words in the land of Judah and in its towns at my restoring their
        fortunes,  \u2018Yahweh bless you, O settlement of righteousness, O hill
        of holiness.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Judah and all of its towns together will live in it, farmers
        and those who travel with the flocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For I will saturate the thirst of the weary, and every person who
        languishes I will replenish.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: The New Covenant'
      title: The New Covenant
      number: 26
      content: 'At this I awoke and looked, and my sleep was pleasant to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CLook, the days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        I will sow the house of Israel and the house of Judah with the seed of humankind,
        and with the seed of animals.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And then as I have watched over them to pull up, and to tear down,
        and to annihilate, and to destroy, and to do evil, so I will watch over them
        to build and to plant,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIn those days they will say no longer, \u2018Parents have eaten
        unripe fruit, and the teeth of the children are set on edge.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But each will die because of his iniquity, everyone who eats the
        unripe fruit, their teeth will be set on edge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Look, the days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand I will
        make a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "not like the covenant that I made with their ancestors on the day
        of my grasping them by their hand, bringing them out from the land of Egypt,
        my covenant that they themselves broke, though I myself was a master over
        them,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CBut this is the covenant that I will make with the house of
        Israel after those days,\u201D declares Yahweh: \u201CI will put my law in
        their inward parts and on their hearts I will write it, and I will be to
        them God, and they themselves will be to me people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And they will no longer teach each one his neighbor, or each one
        his brother, saying, \u2018Know Yahweh,\u2019 for all of them will know me,
        from their smallest and up to their greatest,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cfor
        I will forgive their iniquity and their sin I will no longer remember.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, who gives the sun for light by day, the regulations
        of the moon and the stars for light by night, who stirs up the sea and its
        waves roar\u2014Yahweh of hosts is his name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CIf these rules would cease from before me,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Calso the offspring of Israel would cease from being a nation before
        me forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u201CIf the heavens above can be measured, and
        the foundations of the earth below can be explored, also I will reject all
        the offspring of Israel because of all that they have done,\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CLook, days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand the
        city will be rebuilt for Yahweh, from the Tower of Hananel to the Corner
        Gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And the measuring line will still go out immediately in front of
        it to the hill of Gareb, and it will turn to Goah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And the whole of the valley of the corpses, and the ashes, and all
        the cultivated fields up to the wadi of Kidron, up to the corner of the Gate
        of the Horses toward the east will be holy to Yahweh. It will not be uprooted,
        and it will not be overthrown again forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Buys a Field'
      title: Jeremiah Buys a Field
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh in the tenth year of Zedekiah
        the king of Judah, that was the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now at that time the army of the king of Babylon was laying siege
        to Jerusalem and Jeremiah the prophet was confined in the courtyard of the
        guard that was in the palace of the king of Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "where Zedekiah, the king of Judah, had confined him, saying, \u201CWhy
        are you prophesying, saying, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, I am going
        to give this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he will capture
        it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Zedekiah, the king of Judah, will not escape from the hand of
        the Chaldeans, but surely he will be given into the hand of the king of Babylon,
        and he will speak face to face with him and he will see him eye to eye,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and to Babylon he will bring Zedekiah, and there he will be until
        my attending to him,\u201D declares Yahweh. \u201CIf you fight against the
        Chaldeans, you will not be successful\u201D&nbsp;\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Jeremiah said, \u201CThe word of Yahweh came to me, saying,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Look, Hanamel, the son of Shallum, your uncle, is going to
        come to you, saying, \u201CBuy for yourself my field that is at Anathoth,
        for you have the right of redemption to buy it.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Hanamel, the son of my uncle, came to me, to the courtyard of
        the guard according to the word of Yahweh, and he said to me, \u2018Please
        buy my field that is at Anathoth, that is in the land of Benjamin, for to
        you is the claim of possession, and to you the redemption; buy it for yourself.\u2019
        Then I knew that this was the word of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I bought the field from Hanamel, the son of my uncle, that was
        at Anathoth. And I weighed out to him the money, seventeen silver shekels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I signed on the letter and sealed it, and I called witnesses
        as witness, and I weighed out the money on a set of scales. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then I took the deed of the purchase, the sealed copy containing
        the commandments and the rules, together with the one that was open. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I gave the deed of the purchase to Baruch the son of Neriah,
        the son of Mahseiah, in the presence of Hanamel, the son of my uncle, and
        in the presence of the witnesses who signed the deed of the purchase, in
        the presence of the Judeans who were sitting in the courtyard of the guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I commanded Baruch in their presence, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CTake these
        deeds, this deed of the purchase, the sealed one, and this opened deed, and
        you must put them in an earthenware jar so that they may be kept preserved
        many days.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CHouses and
        fields and vineyards will again be bought in this land.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I prayed to Yahweh\u2014after giving my deed of the purchase
        to Baruch the son of Neriah\u2014saying,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Ah Lord Yahweh! Look, you made the heavens and the earth by
        your great power and by your outstretched arm. Nothing is too difficult for
        you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'showing loyal love to the thousands, and repaying the guilt of parents
        into the laps of their children after them. Powerful, great, mighty, his
        name is Yahweh of hosts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'great in counsel and great in deed, whose eyes are opened to all
        the ways of the children of humankind, to give to each one according to his
        ways and according to the fruit of his deeds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'who accomplished signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, up to this
        day, and in Israel, and among humankind, and you have made for yourself a
        name, as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And you brought out your people Israel from the land of Egypt with
        signs, and with wonders, and with a strong hand, and with an arm stretched
        out, and with great terror. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you gave to them this land, which you swore to their ancestors
        to give to them, a land flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they entered and took possession of it, but they did not listen
        to your voice, and they did not follow your law. They did nothing of all
        that you commanded to them to do, and you caused to happen to them all this
        disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Look, the siege ramps have come up to the city to capture it, and
        the city has been given into the hand of the Chaldeans who are fighting against
        it, because of the sword, the famine, and the plague, and what you spoke
        happened, and look, you are seeing it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Yet you have said to me, Lord Yahweh, \u201CBuy for yourself the
        field with the money, and call witnesses as witness,\u201D though the city
        has been given into the hand of the Chaldeans.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CLook, I am Yahweh, the God of all flesh; is anything too difficult
        for me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh: \u201CLook, I am going to give this city
        into the hand of the Chaldeans, and into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar, the
        king of Babylon, and he will capture it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the Chaldeans, who are fighting against this city, will come
        and set this city on fire, and they will burn it, and the houses where they
        have made smoke offerings on their roofs to Baal, and where they have devoted
        libations to other gods, in order to provoke me to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For the people of Israel and the people of Judah were doing only
        evil in my eyes from their youth, for the people of Israel were only provoking
        me to anger by the work of their hands,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CFor this city has been for me a cause of my anger and of my
        wrath from the day that they built it even until this day, so I will remove
        it from my sight,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "because of all the evil of the people of Israel and the people of
        Judah that they did to provoke me to anger\u2014they, their kings, their
        officials, their priests, and their prophets, and the men of Judah, and the
        inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they have turned to me their backs and not their faces, though
        I have taught them over and over again, but they were not listening to accept
        discipline. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And they set up their abominations in the house that is called by
        my name, to defile it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And they built the high places of Baal that are in the Valley of
        Ben Hinnom to present as offerings their sons and their daughters to Molech,
        which I had not commanded them, and it had not come to my mind to do this
        detestable thing in order to cause Judah to sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CSo now therefore, thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, concerning
        this city, of which you are saying, \u2018It will be given into the hand
        of the king of Babylon by the sword, and by the famine, and by the plague\u2019: "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Look, I am going to gather them from all the lands to which I driven
        them in my anger, and in my fury, and in great wrath, and I will bring them
        back to this place, and I will cause them to dwell in safety.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And they will be for me a people, and I will be for them God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And I will give to them one heart and one way, to revere me forever,
        for good to them, and to their children after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And I will make with them an everlasting covenant that I will not
        turn away from them, my doing good to them, and my reverence I will put in
        their hearts so that they will not turn aside from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And I will rejoice over them to do good to them, and I will plant
        them in this land in faithfulness with all my heart, and with all my inner
        self.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CFor thus says Yahweh, \u2018Just as I have brought to this
        people all this great disaster, so I will bring upon them all the good that
        I promise to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And the fields will be bought in this land of which you are saying,
        \u201CIt is a desolation, without humankind or animals. It has been given
        into the hand of the Chaldeans.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "They will buy fields with money, and they will sign the deeds, and
        they will seal them, and they will call witnesses as witness in the land
        of Benjamin, and in the surroundings of Jerusalem, and in the cities of Judah,
        and in the cities of the hill country, and in the cities of the Shephelah,
        and in the cities of the Negev, for I will restore their fortunes,\u2019
        declares Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fortunes of Judah and Israel Will Be Restored'
      title: The Fortunes of Judah and Israel Will Be Restored
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah a second time while he was
        still held back in the courtyard of the guard, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh who made the earth, Yahweh who formed it to
        establish it, Yahweh is his name: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Call to me, and I will answer you, and I will tell you great
        things and inaccessible things that you have not known.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For thus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, concerning the houses of
        this city and concerning the houses of the kings of Judah, that were torn
        down to make a defense against the siege ramps and against the sword: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018They are coming to fight against the Chaldeans, and to fill
        them with the corpses of the people whom I will strike in my anger and in
        my wrath, for whom I have hidden my face from this city because of all their
        wickedness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Look, I am going to bring healing and health to it, and I will heal
        them, and I will reveal to them abundance of peace and reliability. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will restore the fortunes of Judah and the fortunes of Israel,
        and I will rebuild them as in the beginning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I will cleanse them from all their guilt that they sinned against
        me, and I will forgive all their iniquities that they sinned against me,
        and that they rebelled against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And it will be to me a name of jubilation, a praise, and a glory
        before all the nations of the earth, who will hear all the good that I will
        do for them, and they will fear, and they will tremble because of all the
        good, and because of all the prosperity that I will provide for it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Again will be heard in this place,
        of which you are saying, \u201CIt is a waste, without people and without
        animals,\u201D in the towns of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem that
        are desolate, without people and without inhabitants and without animals,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "the voice of jubilation, and the voice of joy, the voice of the bridegroom,
        and the voice of the bride, the voices of those who say, \u201CPraise Yahweh
        of hosts, for Yahweh is good, for his loyal love is forever,\u201D the voices
        of those who bring thank offerings to the house of Yahweh, for I will restore
        the fortunes of the land as in the beginning,\u2019 says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u2018Again there will be in this waste
        place, without people and animals, and in all its towns, pasture for shepherds
        allowing their flock to lie down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "In the towns of the hill country, in the towns of the Shephelah,
        and in the towns of the Negev, and in the land of Benjamin, and in the surroundings
        of Jerusalem, and in the towns of Judah, flocks will again pass under the
        hands of the counter,\u2019 says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Look, days are coming,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018and I will
        fulfill the good promise that I promised to the house of Israel and to the
        house of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days and in that time I will make a branch of righteousness
        sprout for David, and he will execute justice and righteousness in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "In those days Judah will be saved, and Jerusalem will dwell safely,
        and this is what they shall call it: \u201CYahweh is our righteousness.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For thus says Yahweh: \u2018A man who sits on the throne of the house
        of Israel will not be cut off for David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And for the priests, a man from the Levites who offers burnt offerings
        and who burns grain offerings and who brings sacrifices will not be cut off
        before me forever.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018If you could break my covenant with
        the day, and my covenant with the night, so that day and night would not
        come at their time, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'then my covenant could be broken with David my servant, from having
        a son who could rule on his throne, and with the Levites, the priests, my
        ministers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As the host of heaven cannot be counted, and the sand of the sea
        cannot be measured, so I will make numerous the offspring of David my servant
        and the Levites who minister to me.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CHave you not seen how these people speak, saying, \u2018The
        two clans whom Yahweh chose, he has also rejected them\u2019? Thus they spurn
        my people from being a nation before them any longer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u2018If my covenant with day and with night, the
        regulations of heaven and earth, I had not established, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then the offspring of Jacob and David my servant I would reject,
        from choosing rulers from his offspring over the offspring of Abraham, Isaac,
        and Jacob; for I will restore their fortunes and I will have compassion on
        them.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message for Zedekiah'
      title: A Message for Zedekiah
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, when Nebuchadnezzar the
        king of Babylon, and all his army, with all the kingdoms of the earth under
        the dominion of his hand, and all the peoples were fighting against Jerusalem
        and against all its cities, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u2018Go and say to Zedekiah
        the king of Judah, now you must say to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Look,
        I am going to give this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he
        will burn it with fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And you will not escape from his hand, but surely you will be captured,
        and into his hand you will be given, and you will see the king of Babylon
        eye to eye, and you will speak face to face with him, and to Babylon you
        will go.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "However, hear the word of Yahweh, O Zedekiah, the king of Judah.
        Thus says Yahweh concerning you: \u2018You will not die by the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "In peace you will die, and as there was burning for your ancestors,
        the former kings who were before you, so they will burn for you, and they
        will lament for you, \u201CAlas, lord!\u201D For the word I have spoken,\u2019
        declares Yahweh.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Zedekiah the king of Judah all
        these words in Jerusalem '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Zedekiah\u2019s Covenant Concerning Slaves"
      title: "Zedekiah\u2019s Covenant Concerning Slaves"
      number: 7
      content: "when the army of the king of Babylon was fighting against Jerusalem
        and against all the cities of Judah that were left over\u2014Lachish and
        Azekah, for these remained among the cities of Judah, the cities of fortification. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh after king Zedekiah made
        a covenant with all the people who were in Jerusalem to proclaim release
        to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'to let go each one his male slave and each one his female slave,
        the Hebrew and the free Hebrew, so that no one among the Judeans should enslave
        his fellow countryman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And all the officials and all the people obeyed, who had entered
        into the covenant to let go each one his male slave and each one his female
        slave, not enslaving them again, and they obeyed and they let them go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But afterward they turned back and they brought back the male slaves
        and the female slaves whom they had let go free, and they subdued them as
        male slaves and female slaves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel: \u2018I made a covenant
        with your ancestors on the day of my bringing them out from the land of Egypt,
        from the house of slaves, saying,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAt the end of seven years you must let go each one his fellow
        countryman, the Hebrew who has been sold to you and who has served you six
        years, and you must let him go free from you.\u201D But your ancestors did
        not listen to me, and they did not incline their ears.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And you turned back recently and you did right in my eyes, to proclaim
        release each one to his neighbor, and you made a covenant before me in the
        house that is called by my name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But you turned back and you profaned my name when you brought back
        each one his male slave and each one his female slave, whom you had let go
        free according to their desire, and you subdued them to be to you as male
        slaves and as female slaves.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says Yahweh, \u2018You have not listened to
        me to proclaim release each one to his fellow countryman and each one to
        his neighbor. Look, I am going to proclaim to you a release,\u2019 declares
        Yahweh, \u2018to the sword, to the plague, and to the famine, and I will
        make you a terror to all the kingdoms of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I will make the men who transgressed my covenant, who have not
        kept the words of the covenant that they made before me, like the calf which
        they cut in two and they passed between its parts\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "the officials of Judah, and the officials of Jerusalem, the eunuchs,
        and the priests, and all the people of the land who passed between the parts
        of the calf\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and I will give them into the hand of their enemies, and into the
        hand of the seekers of their lives, and their dead bodies will become as
        food for the birds of the heavens and for the animals of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Zedekiah the king of Judah and his officials I will give into
        the hand of their enemies, and into the hand of the seekers of their lives,
        and into the hand of the army of the king of Babylon, who retreated from
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Look, I am going to command,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018and I will
        bring them back to this city, and they will fight against it, and they will
        capture it, and they will burn it with fire, and the towns of Judah I will
        make a desolation without an inhabitant.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Faithfulness of the Rechabites'
      title: The Faithfulness of the Rechabites
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh in the days of Jehoiakim,
        the son of Josiah, the king of Judah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to the house of the Rechabites, and speak with them, and
        bring them to the house of Yahweh into one of the chambers, and give them
        wine to drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I took Jaazaniah, the son of Jeremiah, the son of Habazziniah,
        and his brothers, and all his sons, and the whole of the house of the Rechabites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and I brought them to the house of Yahweh, into the chamber of the
        sons of Hanan, the son of Igdaliah, the man of God, which was beside the
        chamber of the officials, which was above the chamber of Maaseiah, the son
        of Shallum, the keeper of the threshold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I set before the house of the Rechabites bowls full of wine
        and cups, and I said to them, \u201CDrink wine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But they answered, \u201CWe will not drink wine, for Jonadab, the
        son of Rechab, our ancestor, commanded us, saying, \u2018You shall not drink
        wine, you or your children, forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And you shall not build a house, and you shall not sow seed, and
        you shall not plant a vineyard, and it shall not be for you, but in tents
        you shall live all your days, so that you may live many days on the surface
        of the land where you are dwelling as aliens.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And we obeyed the voice of Jonadab, the son of Rechab, our ancestor,
        in all that he commanded us, not to drink wine all our days, ourselves, our
        wives, our sons, or our daughters, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and not to build houses for our living, and there is not vineyard,
        or field, or seed for us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But we have lived in tents, and we have obeyed, and we have done
        all that Jehonadab, our ancestor, commanded us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But then at the coming up against the land of Nebuchadnezzar the
        king of Babylon, then we said, \u2018Come and let us go to Jerusalem before
        the army of the Chaldeans, and before the army of the Arameans.\u2019 That
        is why we are living in Jerusalem.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018Go and
        say to the people of Judah and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem, \u201CCan
        you not learn a lesson to listen to my words?\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThe words of Jonadab, the son of Rechab, that he commanded
        his descendants to not drink, have been carried out, and they have not drunk
        until this day, for they have obeyed the command of their ancestor. But I
        have spoken to you over and over again, and you have not listened to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I have sent to you all my servants the prophets, I have sent
        them over and over again, saying, \u2018Turn back please each one from his
        evil way, and amend your deeds, and you must not go after other gods to serve
        them, so that you may live on the land that I gave to you and to your ancestors.\u2019
        But you did not incline your ear and you did not listen to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For the descendants of Jonadab, the son of Rechab, have carried out
        the command of their ancestor that he commanded them, but this people did
        not listen to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh, the God of hosts, the God of Israel,
        \u201CLook, I am going to bring to Judah and to all the inhabitants of Jerusalem
        every disaster that I have spoken against them, because I have spoken to
        them and they have not listened, and I have called to them and they have
        not answered.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But to the house of the Rechabites Jeremiah said, \u201CThus says
        Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Because you have listened to the
        command of Jonadab your ancestor, and you have kept all his commands, and
        you have done all that he commanded you,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "therefore thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018A man
        will not be cut off for Jonadab, the son of Rechab, to stand before me always.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll of Jeremiah\u2019s Prophecies"
      title: "Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll of Jeremiah\u2019s Prophecies"
      number: 1
      content: 'And then in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, the king
        of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from Yahweh, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake for yourself a scroll and you must write on it all the
        words that I have spoken to you against Israel, and against Judah, and against
        all the nations, from the day that I spoke to you, from the days of Josiah,
        and until this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Perhaps when the house of Judah hears all the disasters that I am
        planning to do to them, then they may turn back each one from his evil way,
        and I will forgive their guilt and their sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jeremiah called Baruch the son of Neriah, and Baruch wrote from
        the mouth of Jeremiah all the words of Yahweh that he had spoken to him on
        a scroll.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Jeremiah instructed Baruch, saying, \u201CI am held back, I am
        not able to enter the temple of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So you must go and you shall read aloud from the scroll that you
        have written from my mouth the words of Yahweh in the hearing of the people
        in the temple of Yahweh on a day of fast, and also you shall read aloud in
        the hearing of all those of Judah who came from their towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Perhaps their plea will fall before Yahweh and each one will turn
        away from his evil way, for great is the anger and wrath that Yahweh pronounced
        against this people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Baruch the son of Neriah did all that Jeremiah the prophet instructed
        him, to read aloud from the scroll the words of Yahweh in the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And then in the fifth year of Jehoiakim, the son of Josiah, the king
        of Judah, in the ninth month, all the people in Jerusalem and all the people
        who came from the towns of Judah to Jerusalem proclaimed a fast before Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Baruch read aloud from the scroll the words of Jeremiah in the
        temple of Yahweh, in the chamber of Gemariah, the son of Shaphan, the secretary,
        in the upper courtyard at the entrance of the New Gate of the temple of Yahweh
        in the hearing of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Micaiah, the son of Gemariah, the son of Shaphan, heard all
        the words of Yahweh from the scroll, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'he went down to the house of the king, to the chamber of the secretary,
        and look, all the officials were sitting there: Elishama the secretary, and
        Delaiah, the son of Shemaiah, and Elnathan, the son of Achbor, and Gemariah,
        the son of Shaphan, and Zedekiah, the son of Hananiah, and all the other
        officials. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Micaiah told them all the words that he had heard at the reading
        aloud of Baruch from the scroll in the hearing of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then all the officials sent Jehudi, the son of Nethaniah, the son
        of Shelemiah, the son of Cushi, to Baruch, saying, \u201CThe scroll that
        you read aloud from in the hearing of the people, take it in your hand and
        come.\u201D And Baruch the son of Neriah took the scroll in his hand and
        he came to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CSit please and read it aloud in our hearing.\u201D
        So Baruch read aloud in their hearing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And then, the moment of their hearing all the words, they turned
        to one another in alarm and they said to Baruch, \u201CWe must certainly
        report all these words to the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then they asked Baruch, saying, \u201CTell us please, how did you
        write all these words, from his mouth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Baruch said to them, \u201CFrom his mouth. He dictated to me
        all these words and I was writing on the scroll with the ink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the officials said to Baruch, \u201CGo, hide yourself, you and
        Jeremiah, and let not a man know where you are.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they went to the king, to the courtyard, and they put the scroll
        for safe-keeping in the chamber of Elishama the secretary, and they reported
        all the words in the hearing of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the king sent Jehudi to take the scroll, and he took it from
        the chamber of Elishama the secretary, and Jehudi read it aloud in the hearing
        of the king, and in the hearing of all the officials who stood next to the
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now the king was sitting in the quarters of the winter in the ninth
        month, and a fire-pot was burning before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And then, as Jehudi read three or four columns, he would cut it up
        in pieces with the knife of the scribe, and he would throw it into the fire
        that was in the fire-pot until the whole of the scroll was consumed in the
        fire that was in the fire-pot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the king and any of his servants who heard all these words were
        not startled, and they did not tear their garments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And even when Elnathan, and Delaiah, and Gemariah urged the king
        not to burn the scroll, he would not listen to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the king commanded Jerahmeel, the son of the king, and Seraiah,
        the son of Azriel, and Shelemiah, the son of Abdeel, to arrest Baruch the
        secretary and Jeremiah the prophet, but Yahweh hid them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah after the king burned the
        scroll and the words that Baruch wrote from the mouth of Jeremiah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CTake again for yourself another scroll and write on it all
        the former words that were in the first scroll which Jehoiakim, the king
        of Judah, has burned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And concerning Jehoiakim, the king of Judah, you shall say, \u2018Thus
        says Yahweh, \u201CYou have burned this scroll, saying, \u2018Why have you
        written in it, saying, \u201CThe king of Babylon will certainly come and
        he will destroy this land, and he will cause to disappear from it humankind
        and animals\u201D?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh concerning Jehoiakim, the king of Judah,
        \u201CThere will not be for him one who sits on the throne of David. And
        his dead body will be thrown out to the heat in the day and to the frost
        in the night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And I will punish him, and his offspring, and his servants for their
        guilt, and I will bring on them, and on the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and
        on the people of Judah all the disaster with which I have threatened them,
        but they would not listen.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then Jeremiah took another scroll and gave it to Baruch the son of
        Neriah, the secretary, and he wrote on it from the mouth of Jeremiah all
        the words of the scroll that Jehoiakim, the king of Judah, had burned in
        the fire, and furthermore was added to them many words like these. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Babylonians Withdraw to Meet a Threat from Egypt'
      title: The Babylonians Withdraw to Meet a Threat from Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'And king Zedekiah, the son of Josiah, whom Nebuchadnezzar, the king
        of Babylon, had made king, reigned as king in the land of Judah in place
        of Coniah, the son of Jehoiakim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But he and his servants and the people of the land did not listen
        to the words of Yahweh that he spoke by the hand of Jeremiah the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And king Zedekiah sent Jehucal the son of Shelemiah, and Zephaniah
        the son of Maaseiah, the priest, to Jeremiah the prophet, saying, \u201CPlease
        pray for us to Yahweh our God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Jeremiah was coming and going out in the midst of the people
        and they had not put him in the house of imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the army of Pharaoh had come out from Egypt, and the Chaldeans,
        who were laying siege to Jerusalem, heard their report and they withdrew
        from Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah the prophet, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, \u2018This is what you
        shall say to the king of Judah, who sent you to me to inquire of me, \u201CLook,
        the army of Pharaoh, which set out to help you, is going to return to his
        land Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the Chaldeans will return, and they will fight against this city,
        and they will capture it, and they will burn it with fire.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u2018You must not deceive yourselves, saying,
        \u201CSurely the Chaldeans will go from us,\u201D for they will not go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah is Arrested and Put in Prison'
      title: Jeremiah is Arrested and Put in Prison
      number: 10
      content: "For even if you struck the whole army of the Chaldeans who are fighting
        against you, and only men pierced through remained among them, each one in
        his tent, they would rise up and they would burn this city with fire.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And then, at the withdrawing of the army of the Chaldeans from Jerusalem
        before the army of Pharaoh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jeremiah set out from Jerusalem to go to the land of Benjamin to
        receive a portion from there in the midst of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when he was at the Gate of Benjamin, there was a sentry on duty
        whose name was Irijah, the son of Shelemiah, the son of Hananiah, and he
        seized Jeremiah the prophet, saying, \u201CYou are deserting to the Chaldeans!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Jeremiah said, \u201CThat is a lie! I am not deserting to the
        Chaldeans.\u201D But he would not listen to him. So Irijah seized Jeremiah
        and brought him to the officials. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the officials were angry at Jeremiah and they struck him. And
        they put him in prison, in the house of Jonathan the secretary, for they
        had converted it to the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Jeremiah came to the dungeon, even to the vaulted cells, and Jeremiah
        stayed there many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then King Zedekiah sent and fetched him. And the king questioned
        him in secrecy in his house, and he said, \u201CIs there a word from Yahweh?\u201D
        And Jeremiah said, \u201CThere is.\u201D And he said, \u201CYou will be given
        into the hand of the king of Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to King Zedekiah, \u201CWhat did I do wrong to
        you, or to your servants, or to this people, that you have put me in prison?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And where are your prophets who prophesied to you, saying, \u2018The
        king of Babylon will not come against you and against this land\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now then, my lord the king, please let my plea fall before you. You
        must not send me back to the house of Jonathan the secretary, so that I will
        not die there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So King Zedekiah commanded, and they handed Jeremiah over in the
        courtyard of the guard, and they gave to him a round loaf of bread from the
        street of the bakers every day until the finishing of all the bread from
        the city. And Jeremiah stayed in the courtyard of the guard. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah is Thrown into the Pit of Malchiah'
      title: Jeremiah is Thrown into the Pit of Malchiah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Shephatiah the son of Mattan, and Gedaliah the son of Pashhur,
        and Jehucal the son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur the son of Malchiah heard the
        words that Jeremiah was saying to all the people, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, \u2018The one who stays in this city will
        die by the sword, by the famine, and by the plague. But the one who goes
        out to the Chaldeans will live. And his life will be for him as booty, and
        he will live.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u2018Surely this city will be given into the hand
        of the army of the king of Babylon, and he will capture it.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the officials said to the king, \u201CPlease, this man must
        be killed, because he is making slack the hands of the soldiers who are left
        in this city, and the hands of all the people, by speaking to them words
        like these, for this man is not seeking for welfare to this people, but only
        for harm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Zedekiah the king said, \u201CLook, he is in your hand, for the
        king is not able to do a thing against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they took Jeremiah and threw him into the pit of Malchiah, the
        son of the king, which was in the courtyard of the guard. And they let Jeremiah
        down by ropes. Now in the pit there was no water, but only mud, and Jeremiah
        sank in the mud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When Ebed-melech the Cushite, a eunuch who was in the house of the
        king, heard that they had put Jeremiah into the pit\u2014now the king was
        sitting at the Gate of Benjamin\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ebed-melech went out from the house of the king and spoke to the
        king, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CMy lord the king, these men have done evil in all that they
        have done to Jeremiah the prophet, in that they have thrown him into the
        pit, and he will die there because of starvation, for there is no longer
        any bread in the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king commanded Ebed-melech the Cushite, saying, \u201CTake
        with you these thirty men and pull Jeremiah the prophet up from the pit before
        he dies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Ebed-melech took the men with him and went to the palace of the
        king, to a place beneath the storehouse, and he took from there rags and
        worn-out clothes. And he let them down into the pit by ropes to Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Ebed-melech the Cushite said to Jeremiah, \u201CPlease put the
        rags and worn-out clothes under the joints of your arms under the ropes,\u201D
        and Jeremiah did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And they pulled Jeremiah by the ropes and brought him up from the
        pit. And Jeremiah stayed in the courtyard of the guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Zedekiah the king sent and made someone bring Jeremiah the prophet
        to him, to the third entrance that was at the temple of Yahweh. And the king
        said to Jeremiah, \u201CI am asking you something, you must not hide anything
        from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CIf I tell you, will you not
        surely kill me? Besides, if I advise you, you will not listen to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Zedekiah the king swore to Jeremiah in secret, saying, \u201CAs
        Yahweh lives, who has made for us this life, I will not kill you and I will
        not give you into the hand of these men who are seeking your life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of
        hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018If only you will go surrender to the officials
        of the king of Babylon, then you will live, and this city will not be burned
        with fire, and you will live, you and your house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if you do not go surrender to the officials of the king of Babylon,
        then this city will be given into the hand of the Chaldeans, and they will
        burn it with fire, and you will not escape from their hand.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Zedekiah the king said to Jeremiah, \u201CI am afraid of the
        Judeans who have deserted to the Chaldeans, lest they give me into their
        hand and they abuse me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Jeremiah said, \u201CThey will not give you over. Please obey
        the voice of Yahweh with regard to what I am saying to you, and it will go
        well with you, and you will live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if you are refusing to surrender, this is the thing that Yahweh
        has shown me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now look, all the women who remain in the house of the king of Judah
        are being led out to the officials of the king of Babylon. And look, they
        are saying, \u2018Your trusted friends have misled you, and they have prevailed
        against you. Your feet are stuck in the mud, so they turned backward.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And all your wives and your children will be led out to the Chaldeans,
        and you will not escape from their hand, but by the hand of the king of Babylon
        you will be seized, and this city will burn with fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CNo man must know about these
        words so that you will not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And if the officials hear that I have spoken with you, and they come
        to you and say to you, \u2018Please tell us what you said to the king. You
        must not conceal it from us so that we will not kill you. And what did the
        king say to you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then you shall say to them, \u2018I was presenting my plea before
        the king, to not cause me to return to the house of Jonathan to die there.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And all the officials came to Jeremiah and questioned him, and he
        informed them like all these words that the king commanded. So they fell
        silent, for the conversation was not heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Jeremiah stayed in the courtyard of the guard until the day that
        Jerusalem was captured. And it happened that Jerusalem was captured.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'In the ninth year of Zedekiah, the king of Judah, in the tenth month,
        Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon and all his army came against Jerusalem
        and laid siege to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In the eleventh year of Zedekiah, in the fourth month, on the ninth
        day of the month, the city was taken by assault. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And all the officials of the king of Babylon came and sat in the
        Middle Gate: Nergal-sharezer, Samgar-nebo, Sarsechim the chief officer, Nergal-sharezer
        the high official, with all the rest of the officials of the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And then when Zedekiah the king of Judah saw them, and all the soldiers
        with him, they fled and went out at night from the city by the way of the
        garden of the king through the gate between the walls. And they went out
        toward the Jordan Valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued after them and overtook Zedekiah
        in the plains of Jericho. And they took him and brought him up to Nebuchadnezzar
        the king of Babylon at Riblah in the land of Hamath. And he pronounced sentence
        on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the king of Babylon slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah at Riblah
        before his eyes. The king of Babylon also slaughtered all the nobles of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then he blinded the eyes of Zedekiah and tied him up with bronze
        fetters to bring him to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Chaldeans burned the palace of the king and the houses of
        the people with fire and broke down the walls of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the rest of the people who were left in the city, and those
        deserting who had deserted to him, and the rest of the people who remained,
        Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, deported to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And some of the poor people, who had nothing, Nebuzaradan, the captain
        of the guard, left in the land of Judah. And he gave them vineyards and fields
        on that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon commanded concerning Jeremiah
        through Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTake him and set your eyes on him. And you must not do something
        bad to him, but only that which he speaks to you, so do with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, sent word, along with Nebushazban
        the chief officer, and Nergal-sharezer the high official, and all the chief
        officers of the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Ebed-melech is Rewarded for His Faith'
      title: Ebed-melech is Rewarded for His Faith
      number: 14
      content: 'And they sent and took Jeremiah from the courtyard of the guard and
        gave him to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, to take him to
        the house, so he stayed in the midst of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah at his confinement in the
        courtyard of the guard, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo and say to Ebed-melech the Cushite, saying, \u2018Thus says
        Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CLook, I am about to bring my words
        to pass against this city for evil and not for good. And they will be before
        you on that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But I will rescue you on that day,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        you will not be given into the hand of the men of whom you are frightened.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For surely I will save you, and you will not fall by the sword. But
        your life will be for you as booty because you have trusted in me,\u201D
        declares Yahweh.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Decides to Remain in the Land'
      title: Jeremiah Decides to Remain in the Land
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from Yahweh after Nebuzaradan, the
        captain of the guard, had let him go from Ramah, where he had been taken
        bound in chains in the midst of all the exiles of Jerusalem and Judah who
        were being deported to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the captain of the guard took Jeremiah and said to him, \u201CYahweh
        your God threatened this disaster to this place, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and now he has brought it about, and Yahweh has done just as he threatened.
        Because you sinned against Yahweh and did not listen to his voice, so this
        thing has happened to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And so then look, I have released you today from the chains that
        were on your hands. If it is good in your eyes to come with me to Babylon,
        then come, and I will take care of you. But if it is bad in your eyes to
        come with me to Babylon, then refrain. Look, the whole land is before you.
        To wherever it is good and right in your eyes to go, then go there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "While he still had not turned back, Nebuzaradan added, \u201CReturn
        to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, whom the king of Babylon
        has appointed in an official position over the towns of Judah, and stay with
        him in the midst of the people. Or to wherever it is right in your eyes to
        go, then go there.\u201D Then the captain of the guard gave him an allowance
        of provisions and a present, and let him go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Assassination of Gedaliah'
      title: The Assassination of Gedaliah
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jeremiah went to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, at Mizpah and stayed
        with him in the midst of the people who were left in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When all the commanders of the armies who were in the open country
        and their men heard that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah the son
        of Ahikam in an official position in the land, and that he had put him in
        charge of men, and women, and little children, and of the poor of the land,
        of all those who had not been deported to Babylon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "then they went to Gedaliah at Mizpah\u2014Ishmael the son of Nethaniah,
        and Johanan, and Jehonathan the son of Kareah, and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth,
        and the sons of Ephai the Netophathite, and Jezaniah the son of the Maacathite,
        they and their men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, swore to them
        and to their men, saying, \u201CYou must not be afraid of serving the Chaldeans.
        Stay in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it will go well with
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As for me, look, I am staying at Mizpah to represent you before the
        Chaldeans who come to us. But you, gather wine and summer fruit and oil,
        and put them in your vessels, and live in your towns that you have seized.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And also all the Judeans who were in Moab, and among the Ammonites,
        and in Edom, and who were in all the lands, when they heard that the king
        of Babylon had given a remnant to Judah and that he had appointed Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, in an official position over them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then all the Judeans returned from all the places to which they were
        scattered. And they came to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah at Mizpah, and
        they gathered wine and summer fruit that yielded in great abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies
        who were in the open country came to Gedaliah at Mizpah '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and said to him, \u201CAre you at all aware that Baalis, the king
        of the Ammonites, has sent Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, to kill you?\u201D
        But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam would not believe them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Johanan the son of Kareah said to Gedaliah in secrecy at Mizpah,
        saying, \u201CPlease let me go and kill Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and
        nobody will know. Why should he kill you, so that all of Judah who are gathered
        to you will be scattered, and the remnant of Judah will perish?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam said to Johanan the son of Kareah,
        \u201CYou must not do this thing, for you are telling a lie about Ishmael.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' And then in the seventh month Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, the
        son of Elishama, from the offspring of the kingship, and one of the chief
        officers of the king, came to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam at Mizpah, along
        with ten men. And they ate bread together there at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Ishmael the son of Nethaniah got up, along with the ten men who
        were with him, and they struck Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan,
        with the sword and killed him whom the king of Babylon had appointed in an
        official position over the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Massacre of the Mourners'
      title: The Massacre of the Mourners
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Ishmael killed all the Judeans who were with Gedaliah at Mizpah,
        along with the Chaldeans who were found there, the soldiers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And then on the second day of the killing of Gedaliah\u2014and no
        one knew\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then men came from Shechem, from Shiloh, and from Samaria, eighty
        men with shaven beards and torn garments, who had cut themselves with blades,
        having grain offerings and frankincense in their hands to bring to the temple
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Ishmael the son of Nethaniah came out to meet them from Mizpah,
        weeping as he came. And then as he was meeting them, he said to them, \u201CCome
        to Gedaliah, the son of Ahikam.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And then, the moment of their coming to the middle of the city, then
        Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, along with the men who were with him, slaughtered
        them and threw them to the middle of the pit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But ten men were found among them, and they said to Ishmael, \u201CYou
        must not kill us, for we have hidden treasures in the field, wheat, and barley,
        and oil, and honey. So he refrained and he did not kill them in the midst
        of their fellow countrymen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the pit into which Ishmael threw all the corpses of the men whom
        he had killed along with Gedaliah was the same one that King Asa had made
        because of Baasha the king of Israel, who was against him. Ishmael the son
        of Nethaniah filled it with the slain ones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Ishmael took captive all the rest of the people who were in
        Mizpah, the daughters of the king and all the people who were left at Mizpah,
        over whom Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, had appointed Gedaliah the
        son of Ahikam. And Ishmael took them captive and set out to cross over to
        the Ammonites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies
        who were with him, heard all the evil that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah had
        done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then they took all the men and went to fight against Ishmael the
        son of Nethaniah. And they met him at the great pool that is in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And then, the moment that all the people who were with Ishmael saw
        Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies who were with
        him, they were glad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So all the people whom Ishmael had taken captive from Mizpah turned
        around and returned and went to Johanan the son of Kareah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But Ishmael the son of Nethaniah escaped with eight men from Johanan,
        and they went to the Ammonites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies
        who were with him took from Mizpah all the rest of the people whom he had
        recovered from Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, after he had killed Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam, strong men, soldiers, and women, and little children,
        and eunuchs whom he brought back from Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they set out and stayed at the lodging place of Chimham that
        is near Bethlehem, intending to go to Egypt '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'because of the Chaldeans. For they were afraid of them, because Ishmael
        the son of Nethaniah had killed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, whom the king
        of Babylon had appointed in an official position over the land. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Remnant Asks Jeremiah to Pray to Yahweh for Direction'
      title: The Remnant Asks Jeremiah to Pray to Yahweh for Direction
      number: 1
      content: 'Then all the commanders of the armies, and Johanan the son of Kareah,
        and Jezaniah the son of Hoshaiah, and all the people from the smallest to
        the greatest, approached '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said to Jeremiah the prophet, \u201CMay our plea please fall
        before you, and pray for us to Yahweh your God, for all this remnant, for
        we are left but a few of many, as your eyes are seeing us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And let Yahweh your God inform us the way in which we should go and
        the thing that we should do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Jeremiah the prophet said to them, \u201CI have heard. Look,
        I am going to pray to Yahweh your God according to your words, and then all
        the words that Yahweh answers you I will tell you; I will not withhold from
        you a word.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then they said to Jeremiah, \u201CMay Yahweh be against us as a true
        and faithful witness if we do not do according to all the words that Yahweh
        sends you for us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Remnant Rejects the Word of Yahweh'
      title: The Remnant Rejects the Word of Yahweh
      number: 6
      content: "Whether good or bad, we will listen to the voice of Yahweh our God,
        to whom we are sending you, so that it may go well with us when we listen
        to the voice of Yahweh our God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And then at the end of ten days the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he summoned Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the commanders
        of the armies who were with him, and all the people from the smallest to
        the greatest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and said to them, \u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, to whom
        you sent me to cause your plea to fall before him:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018If only you will stay in this land, then I will build you and
        I will not tear you down, and I will plant you and I will not pluck you up,
        for I relent of the disaster that I have brought to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "You must not be afraid of the king of Babylon whom you are afraid
        of. You must not be afraid of him,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018for I am
        with you to save you and to deliver you from his hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will show you compassion, and he will have compassion on you
        and will restore you to your soil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But if you are saying, \u201CWe will not stay in this land,\u201D
        so as to not listen to the voice of Yahweh your God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "saying, \u201CNo, for we will go to the land of Egypt where we will
        not see war, and we will not hear the sound of a horn, and we will not be
        hungry for bread, and there we will stay,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "then therefore hear the word of Yahweh, O remnant of Judah. Thus
        says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CIf you are determined to go
        to Egypt, and you go to dwell as aliens there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then it will be that the sword that you are in fear of will overtake
        you there in the land of Egypt, and the famine that you are anxious of will
        pursue after you there into Egypt, and there you will die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So all the people who are determined to go to Egypt to dwell as aliens
        there will die by the sword, by the famine, and by the plague, and there
        will not be for them an escapee or a survivor from the disaster that I am
        bringing upon them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CAs my anger
        and my wrath were poured out on the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so my wrath
        will pour out on you at your going to Egypt, and you will become a curse,
        and a horror, and a curse formula, and a disgrace, and you will no longer
        see this place.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Yahweh has spoken to you, O remnant of Judah, \u2018You must not
        go to Egypt.\u2019 You must certainly know that I have warned you today  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "that you have made a fatal mistake, for you sent me to Yahweh your
        God, saying, \u2018Pray for us to Yahweh our God, and all that Yahweh our
        God says, so tell us and we will do it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So I have told you today, and you have not listened to the voice
        of Yahweh your God, or of anything that he sent me for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now then, certainly you must know that by the sword, by the famine,
        and by the plague you will die in the place where you desire to go, to dwell
        as aliens there.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' And then, when Jeremiah had finished speaking to all the people
        all the words of Yahweh their God, for which Yahweh their God had sent him
        to them with all these words, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Azariah the son of Hoshaiah, and Johanan the son of Kareah, and all
        the insolent men spoke, saying to Jeremiah, \u201CYou are telling a lie!
        Yahweh our God did not send you, saying, \u2018You must not go to Egypt to
        dwell as aliens there.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Baruch the son of Neriah is inciting you against us in order
        to give us into the hand of the Chaldeans, to kill us and to deport us to
        Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies,
        and all the people did not listen to the voice of Yahweh to stay in the land
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the armies
        took all the remnant of Judah who had returned from all the nations to which
        they had been scattered to dwell as aliens in the land of Judah\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "the men, and the women, and the little children, and the daughters
        of the king, and everyone whom Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had left
        with Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, and Jeremiah the prophet,
        and Baruch the son of Neriah\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Throne of Nebuchadnezzar Will be Set Up at Tahpanhes'
      title: The Throne of Nebuchadnezzar Will be Set Up at Tahpanhes
      number: 7
      content: 'and they came into the land of Egypt, for they did not listen to
        the voice of Yahweh. And they came up to Tahpanhes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the word of Yahweh came to Jeremiah in Tahpanhes, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTake in your hands large stones and bury them in the mortar
        in the clay floor that is at the entrance of the palace of Pharaoh in Tahpanhes
        before the eyes of the people of the Judeans, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel:
        \u201CLook, I am going to send and take Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon,
        my servant, and I will set his throne above these stones that I have hidden.
        And he will spread out his canopy over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he will come and ravage the land of Egypt, and deliver those
        who are appointed for the plague, to the plague, and those who are appointed
        for the captivity, to the captivity, and those who are appointed for the
        sword, to the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then he will kindle a fire in the temples of the gods of Egypt, and
        he will burn them and take them captive. And he will wrap up the land of
        Egypt just as the shepherd wraps up his cloak. And he will go forth from
        there in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he will break the stone pillars of Heliopolis, which is in the
        land of Egypt. And he will burn the temples of the gods of Egypt with fire.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message of Rebuke for the Rebellious Remnant'
      title: A Message of Rebuke for the Rebellious Remnant
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the Judeans who were
        living in the land of Egypt, who were living at Migdol, and Tahpanhes, and
        Memphis, and in the land of Pathros, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018You yourselves
        have seen all the disaster that I have brought on Jerusalem, and on all the
        towns of Judah. And look, they are a site of ruins this day, and there is
        not in them an inhabitant, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'because of their wickedness that they committed to provoke me to
        anger by going to make smoke offerings, serving other gods whom they had
        not known, neither they, you, or your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I sent to you all my servants the prophets, sending over and
        over again, saying, \u201CPlease, you must not do this detestable thing that
        I hate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But they did not listen and they did not incline their ears to turn
        back from their wickedness, to not make smoke offerings to other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So my wrath and my anger were poured out and burned in the towns
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, and they became as a site of ruins,
        as a desolation, as they are this day.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So then, thus says Yahweh, the God of hosts, the God of Israel, \u2018Why
        are you doing great harm to yourselves, to cut off for yourselves man and
        woman, child and suckling, from the midst of Judah, to not leave over for
        yourselves a remnant, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'provoking me to anger with the works of your hands, to make smoke
        offerings to other gods in the land of Egypt where you have come to dwell
        as aliens, so as to cut off yourselves, and so that you are becoming as a
        curse, and as a disgrace among all the nations of the earth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you forgotten the wicked things of your ancestors, and the wicked
        things of the kings of Judah, and the wicked things of their wives, and your
        wicked things, and the wicked things of your wives, which they committed
        in the land of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They have not shown contrition up to this day, and they have not
        shown reverence, and they have not walked in my law and in my statutes that
        I set before you and before your ancestors.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018Look,
        I am determined to bring disaster on you, even to exterminate all Judah."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will take away the remnant of Judah who are determined to come
        to the land of Egypt to dwell as aliens there, and everyone will perish.
        They will fall in the land of Egypt by the sword; they will perish by the
        famine, from the smallest to the greatest. By the sword and by the famine
        they will die and become as a curse, as a horror, and as a curse, and as
        a disgrace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So I will punish those who live in the land of Egypt just as I have
        punished Jerusalem, with the sword, with the famine, and with the plague. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And there will not be a survivor or an escapee of the remnant of
        Judah, those who have come to dwell as an alien there in the land of Egypt,
        to return to the land of Judah where they are longing to return to dwell
        there, for they will not turn back, but only some survivors.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then all the men who knew that their wives were making smoke offerings
        to other gods, and all the women who stood by, a great assembly, and all
        the people who lived in the land of Egypt in Pathros, answered Jeremiah,
        saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CConcerning the word that you have spoken to us in the name
        of Yahweh, we are not going to listen to you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But certainly we will do everything that went out from our mouths,
        to make smoke offerings to the queen of heaven and to pour out to her libations
        just as we did, we, and our ancestors, our kings, and our officials, in the
        towns of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, for then we had enough to
        eat, and we were well-off, and we did not see disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But since we stopped making smoke offerings to the queen of heaven
        and pouring out libations to her, we have lacked everything, and by the sword
        and by the famine we have perished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And indeed, when we were making smoke offerings to the queen of heaven
        and pouring out to her libations, was it not with the consent of our husbands
        that we made for her sacrificial cakes marked with her image, and we poured
        out to her libations?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Jeremiah said to all the people, to the men and to the women,
        and to all the people who answered him a word, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThe offering that you made, smoke offerings in the towns of
        Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, you, and your ancestors, your kings,
        and your officials, and the people of the land, did not Yahweh remember them,
        and did it not come to his mind?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Yahweh was no longer able to bear it, because of the evil of
        your deeds, because of the detestable things that you committed. Thus your
        land became as a site of ruins, and as a horror, and as a curse, without
        inhabitants, as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Because of the fact that you made smoke offerings, and that you sinned
        against Yahweh, and you did not listen to the voice of Yahweh, and you have
        not walked in his law, and in his statute, and in his legal provisions, therefore
        this disaster has happened to you, as it is this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to all the people and to all the women, \u201CHear
        the word of Yahweh, all Judah who are in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, saying, \u2018You and
        your wives have promised with your mouths and with your hands you have fulfilled,
        saying, \u201CWe certainly will carry out our vows that we vowed, to make
        smoke offerings to the queen of the heavens, and to pour out to her libations.\u201D
        You must certainly keep your vows and you must certainly carry out your vows.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore hear the word of Yahweh, all Judah, those who live in the
        land of Egypt: \u2018Look, I hereby swear by my great name,\u2019 says Yahweh,
        \u2018surely my name will no longer be called in the mouth of any man of
        Judah, saying, \u201Cas the Lord Yahweh lives,\u201D in all the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Look, I am going to watch over them for harm and not for good, and
        all people of Judah who are in the land of Egypt will perish by the sword
        and by the famine until their perishing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the survivors of the sword will return from the land of Egypt
        to the land of Judah few in number. And all the remnant of Judah who have
        come to the land of Egypt to dwell as aliens there will know whose word will
        endure, from me or from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And this will be to you the sign,\u2019 declares Yahweh, \u2018that
        I am going to punish you in this place, so that you may know that surely
        my words will endure against you for evil.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u2018Look, I am going to give Pharaoh Hophra,
        the king of Egypt, into the hand of his enemies, and into the hand of those
        who seek his life, just as I gave Zedekiah the king of Judah into the hand
        of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, his enemy and the one who sought his
        life.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message for Baruch'
      title: A Message for Baruch
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Baruch, the son of Neriah,
        at his writing these words on a scroll from the mouth of Jeremiah, in the
        fourth year of Jehoiakim, the son of Josiah, the king of Judah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh, the God of Israel, to you, O Baruch: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018You said, \u201CWoe please to me, for Yahweh has added sorrow
        to my pain. I am weary in my groaning and I do not find rest.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus you will say to him: \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, what
        I have built I am about to tear down, and what I have planted I am about
        to pluck up, it is all the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And you, do you seek great things for yourself? Do not seek great
        things, for look, I am about to bring disaster upon all flesh,\u201D declares
        Yahweh, \u201Cbut to you I will give your life as booty in all the places
        where you may go.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Messages Concerning Egypt'
      title: Messages Concerning Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of Yahweh that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning the
        nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Concerning Egypt: Concerning the army of Pharaoh Neco, the king of
        Egypt, which was by the Euphrates River at Carchemish, which Nebuchadnezzar
        the king of Babylon defeated in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah,
        the king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CPrepare small shield and shield, and approach for the battle! "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Harness the horses and mount the steeds! And take your stand with
        helmets! Polish the spears! Put on the body armor! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Why do I see them terrified? They are turning back and their warriors
        are beaten down. And they have fled to a place of refuge and they do not
        turn back. Terror is from all around,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The swift cannot flee, and the warrior cannot escape. They have stumbled
        and they have fallen, by the bank of the Euphrates River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who is this that rises like the Nile, like the rivers whose waters
        surge? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Egypt rises like the Nile, even like the rivers whose waters surge.
        And he says, \u201CLet me rise, let me cover the earth, let me destroy cities,
        and the inhabitants in them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Go up, O horses, and drive madly, O chariots,  and let the warriors
        go forth; Cush and Put, who wield the small shield, and Lud, who wield and
        bend the bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For that day is to the Lord Yahweh of hosts a day of retribution,
        to take revenge on his foes. And the sword will devour and be satisfied,
        and it will drink its fill of their blood, for a sacrifice is for the Lord
        Yahweh of hosts in the land of the north by the Euphrates River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Go up to Gilead and take balm, O virgin of the daughter of Egypt.
        In vain you make use of many medicines; there is no healing for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The nations have heard your shame, and your cry of lament fills the
        earth. For warrior has stumbled against warrior, together they have fallen,
        the two of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The word that Yahweh spoke to Jeremiah the prophet about the coming
        of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon to attack the land of Egypt: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CDeclare in Egypt, and proclaim in Migdol, and proclaim in Memphis
        and in Tahpanhes, say, \u2018Take your stand and be prepared, for the sword
        will devour those all around you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Why are your bulls defeated? He did not stand because Yahweh thrust
        him down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He multiplied the ones stumbling. Furthermore, each one fell to his
        neighbor, and said, \u2018Stand up, and let us return to our people and to
        the land of our birth, because of the presence of the sword of the oppressor.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They will call there, \u2018Pharaoh, the king of Egypt is but a roar,
        he missed the opportunity.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "As I live,\u201D declares the king, Yahweh of hosts is his name,
        \u201Cone will come like Tabor among the mountains and like Carmel by the
        sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pack your baggage for exile, O inhabitants of the daughter of Egypt,
        for Memphis will become as a horror, and it will be destroyed, without inhabitant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Egypt is a beautiful heifer, but a gadfly from the north will come
        against her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Even her mercenaries in her midst are like calves of fattening, for
        they also have turned away, they have fled together. They stand not, for
        the day of their calamity has come, the time of their punishment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Her sound is like a snake that glides away, for they march in force.
        And with axes they come to her like those who chop trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They will cut down her forest,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cfor it
        is impenetrable.  Yes, they are more numerous than locusts,  and they are
        without number.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The daughter of Egypt will be ashamed, she will be given into the
        hand of the people of the north.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, said, \u201CLook, I am going
        to punish Amon of Thebes, and Pharaoh, and Egypt, and her gods, and her kings,
        even Pharaoh and those who trust in him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And I will give them into the hand of the seekers of their lives,
        and into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, and into the hand
        of his troops. But afterward it will be inhabited, as in days of old,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBut as for you, my servant Jacob, you must not be afraid, and
        Israel, you must not be dismayed, for look, I am going to save you from far,
        and your offspring from the land of their captivity. And Jacob will return,
        and he will be quiet, and he will be at ease, and without one who makes him
        afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You must not be afraid, my servant Jacob,\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cfor I am with you. For I will make a complete destruction in all the
        nations where I scattered you, but you I will not make a complete destruction,
        though I will chastise you to the measure, and I will certainly not leave
        you unpunished.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message Concerning the Philistines'
      title: A Message Concerning the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of Yahweh that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning the
        Philistines before Pharaoh attacked Gaza. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CLook, waters are rising from the north, and
        they will become as a raging torrent, and they will overflow the land, and
        that which fills it, the city and those who live in it. And the people will
        cry out, and every inhabitant of the land will wail, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'from the sound of the stamping of the hoofs of his stallions, from
        the clattering of his chariots,  the noise of their wheels. Fathers do not
        turn to their children because of the slackness of their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because of the day that is coming to destroy all the Philistines,
        to cut off from Tyre and from Sidon every survivor who could help, for Yahweh
        is destroying the Philistines, the remnant of the coastland of Caphtor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Baldness has come upon Gaza, Ashkelon is destroyed. O remnant of
        their valley, how long will you cut yourself with a blade? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ah, sword of Yahweh, how long will you not be quiet? Gather to your
        sheath, keep quiet and stand still. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How can you be quiet when Yahweh has given an order to it? Against
        Ashkelon and against the shore of the sea, there he has appointed it.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message Concerning Moab'
      title: A Message Concerning Moab
      number: 1
      content: "Concerning Moab, thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CWoe
        to Nebo, for it is devastated. It is ashamed, Kiriathaim is captured. Misgab
        is ashamed, and it is filled with terror. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The glory of Moab is no longer. In Heshbon they planned evil against
        her. Come and let us cut her off from being a nation. Also, Madmen, you will
        be silent. After you will go the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sound of a cry of distress arises from Horonaim, devastation
        and great destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moab is broken, her little ones make heard a cry for help. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the ascent of Luhith, in weeping they go weeping, For on the
        slope of Horonaim they have heard the distresses of the cry of distress of
        the destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Flee! Save your life! For you must not be like the juniper tree in
        the desert. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For because of your trusting in your works and in your treasures,
        even you yourselves will be taken, and Chemosh will go out into the exile,
        his priests and his officials together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the destroyer will come to every town, and a town will not escape.
        And the valley will be destroyed, and the plain will be destroyed, as Yahweh
        has spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Give salt for Moab, for certainly she will go to ruin, and her towns
        will become as a desolation, without an inhabitant in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The one who does the work of Yahweh with slackness is cursed, and
        the one who keeps away blood from his sword is cursed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moab has been at ease from his youth, and he has been quiet on his
        dregs, and he has not been poured out from vessel to vessel, and he has not
        gone into exile. Therefore his taste has remained unchanged, and his fragrance
        has not changed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore look, days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        I will send to him decanters,  and they will decant him, and his vessels
        they will empty out, and their jars they will smash. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Moab will be ashamed of Chemosh, just as the house of Israel
        were ashamed of Bethel, their trust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "How can you say, \u2018we are warriors, and men of might for the
        battle.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Moab is destroyed, and his towns have gone up, and the choice of
        his young men have gone down to the slaughtering,\u201D declares the King,
        Yahweh of hosts is his name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThe disaster of Moab is near to come, and his disaster approaches
        very quickly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Mourn for him, all his surroundings, and all those who knew his name.
        Say, \u2018How the staff of might is broken, the staff of glory.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Come down from glory and sit on the parched ground, O inhabitant,
        daughter of Dibon, for the destroyer of Moab has come up against you, he
        has destroyed your fortifications. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Stand by the road and watch, O inhabitant of Aroer. Ask the man who
        is fleeing and the woman who is escaping, say, \u2018What has happened?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Moab is ashamed, for it is filled with terror. Wail and cry out,
        tell it by Arnon that Moab is devastated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Judgment has also come to the land of the plain, to Holon, and to
        Jahaz, and on Mephaath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and on Dibon, and on Nebo, and on Beth-diblathaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and on Kiriathaim, and on Beth-gamul, and on Beth-meon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and on Kerioth, and on Bozrah, and on all the towns of the land of
        Moab, the far and the near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The horn of Moab is cut off and his arm is broken,\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CMake him drunk, because he magnified himself against Yahweh,
        and let Moab wallow in his vomit. And he also will become a laughingstock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now was not Israel the laughingstock to you? Or was he found among
        thieves? For as often as you spoke over him you shook your head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Leave the towns and dwell on the rock, O inhabitants of Moab, and
        be like the dove, it nests on the sides of the mouth of a ravine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "We have heard of the pride of Moab \u2014he is very proud\u2014 his
        height, and his pride, and his arrogance, and the haughtiness of his heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "I know his insolence,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand his boastings
        are false;  they act falsely.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore over Moab I wail, and for all of Moab I cry out, for the
        people of Kir-heres I moan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'More than the weeping of Jazer I weep for you, O vine Sibmah. Your
        branches cross over the sea, up to the sea of Jazer they reach. Upon your
        summer fruit and upon your vintage the destroyer has fallen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And joy and rejoicing have been taken away from the fruitful land,
        even from the land of Moab. And the wine from the wine presses I have caused
        to disappear. He will not tread with exuberant shouts.  Exuberant shouts
        will not be exuberant shouts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'From the cry for help of Heshbon, up to Elealeh, up to Jahaz, they
        give their voice, from Zoar up to Horonaim, up to Eglath-shelishiyah, for
        even the waters of Nimrim have become as a desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And I will cause to disappear for Moab,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cthe
        one who presents a sacrifice at a high place, and the one who burns a smoke
        offering to his gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Therefore my heart moans for Moab like the flute.  It moans for the
        people of Kir-heres like the flute.  Therefore the wealth they gained has
        perished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For on every head is baldness, and every beard is trimmed. On all
        the hands, slashes, and on the loins, sackcloth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "On all the roofs of Moab, and in its public squares, there is wailing
        everywhere. For I have broken Moab like a vessel, there is no delight in
        it,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CHow it is filled with terror! How they wail! How Moab has turned
        his back! He is disgraced! So Moab has become as a derision, and as a terror
        for all his surrounding peoples.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, like an eagle he will swoop down,
        and he will spread out his wings against Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Kerioth will be taken, and the strongholds will be conquered, and
        the hearts of the warriors of Moab will be on that day like the heart of
        a woman who is in labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And Moab will be destroyed from being a people, because against Yahweh
        he magnified himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Dread, and pit, and a trapping net are against you, O inhabitant
        of Moab,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CHe who flees before the dread will fall into the pit, and the
        one who climbs up from the pit will be caught in the trapping net, for I
        will bring on Moab the year of their punishment,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CIn the shadow of Heshbon fugitives stand without strength,
        for a fire has gone out from Heshbon, and a flame from Sihon. And it has
        eaten the forehead of Moab, and the skulls of the people of tumult. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Woe to you, Moab! The people of Chemosh have perished. For your sons
        have been taken into captivity, and your daughters into captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Yet I will restore the fortunes of Moab in the last of the days,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. Thus far is the judgment of Moab. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message Concerning Ammon'
      title: A Message Concerning Ammon
      number: 1
      content: "Concerning the Ammonites: Thus says Yahweh, \u201CAre there no sons
        for Israel? Or is there no heir for him? Why has Milcom taken possession
        of Gad, and his people dwelled in its towns? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore look, days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        I will sound against Rabbah, the Ammonites,  the alarm of the war, and it
        will become as a mound of desolation, and its daughters will burn in the
        fire. Then Israel will dispossess his dispossessors,\u201D says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CWail, Heshbon, for Ai is devastated. Cry out, O daughters of
        Rabbah, put on sackcloth. Lament and run back and forth among the walls.
        For Milcom will go into exile, his priests and his officials together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Why do you boast in your valleys? Your valleys are ebbing. O unfaithful
        daughter, who trusted in her treasures, who said, \u2018Who will come against
        me?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Look, I am going to bring dread on you,\u201D declares Lord Yahweh
        of hosts, \u201Cfrom all your surrounding neighbors. And you will be scattered,
        each one before it,  and there is no one who gathers the fugitives.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A Message Concerning Edom'
      title: A Message Concerning Edom
      number: 6
      content: "Yet afterward I will restore the fortunes of the Ammonites,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Concerning Edom, thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CIs there no longer
        wisdom in Teman? Has counsel become lost from those who understand? Is their
        wisdom rotting? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Flee! Turn back! Get down low!  O inhabitants of Dedan. For I will
        bring upon him the disaster of Esau at the time when I will punish him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If grape-gatherers come to you, would they not leave gleanings? If
        thieves in the night, they destroy only enough for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But I have stripped Esau bare. I have uncovered his hiding places,
        and he is not able to hide himself. His offspring are devastated, along with
        his brothers, and his neighbors, and he is no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Leave your orphans. I will let them live. And your widows, let them
        trust in me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, those who are not condemned to
        drink the cup must certainly drink it. And are you the one who will go entirely
        unpunished? You will not go unpunished, for you must certainly drink it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I have sworn by myself,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cthat Bozrah
        will become as a horror, as a disgrace, as a waste, and as a curse. And all
        her towns will be everlasting sites of ruins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I have heard a message from Yahweh, and a messenger has been sent
        among the nations. \u201CGather and come against her, and rise for the battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CFor look, I will make you small among the nations, despised
        by the humankind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Your terror has deceived you, the pride of your heart, O you who
        dwell in the clefts of the rock, you who seize the height of the hill. Though
        you make your nest high like the eagle, from there I will bring you down,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnd Edom will become as a horror, everyone who passes by it
        will be appalled, and will hiss because of all its blows. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "As the overthrow of Sodom and Gomorrah and their neighbors,\u201D
        says Yahweh, \u201Cno one will live there, and the son of humankind will
        not dwell as an alien in it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Look, like a lion he comes up from the thickets of the Jordan to
        a pastureland by a constantly flowing stream.  So I will chase him away hurriedly
        from it. And whoever is chosen I will appoint over it. For who is like me,
        and who can summon me? And who is this, the shepherd who can stand before
        me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Therefore hear the plan of Yahweh that he has planned against Edom,
        and his plans that he has planned against the inhabitants of Teman. Surely
        they will drag them away, the little ones of the flock. Surely he will cause
        to be desolated over them their grazing place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The earth will quake from the sound of their falling. A cry of distress!
        Their voice will be heard at the Red Sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: A Message Concerning Damascus'
      title: A Message Concerning Damascus
      number: 22
      content: 'Look, like an eagle he will go up and he will swoop down, and he
        will spread out his wings against Bozrah. And the heart of the warriors of
        Edom will be in that day like the heart of a woman who is in labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Concerning Damascus: \u201CHamath and Arpad are ashamed, for they
        have heard bad news; they melt. There is concern in the sea. It is not able
        to keep quiet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Damascus has grown slack. She has turned away to flee and panic.
        Anxiety has seized her, and labor pains have grasped her, like a woman in
        labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'How the city of praise has not been abandoned! The city of my joy! '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore her young men will fall in her public squares, and all
        the soldiers will perish in that day,\u201D declares Yahweh of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: A Message Concerning Kedar and the Kingdoms of Hazor'
      title: A Message Concerning Kedar and the Kingdoms of Hazor
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CAnd I will kindle a fire at the wall of Damascus, and it will
        devour the citadel fortresses of Ben-hadad.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Concerning Kedar and concerning the kingdoms of Hazor that Nebuchadnezzar
        the king of Babylon defeated. Thus says Yahweh: \u201CRise up, go up against
        Kedar and destroy the people of the east. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "They will take their tents, and their flocks, their tent curtains,
        and all their equipment, and their camels they will carry away for themselves,
        and they will call to them, \u2018Terror is from all around.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Flee! Wander far away! Get down low!  O inhabitants of Hazor,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. \u201CFor Nebuchadnezzar, the king of Babylon, has planned
        a plan against you. And he has schemed a scheme against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Rise up, go up against a nation which is at ease, living securely,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. \u201CThere are no gates and there are no bars for them,
        they dwell alone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And their camels will become as plunder, and the multitude of their
        livestock as spoil. And I will scatter to every wind those who are trimmed
        to the side, and from every side I will bring their disaster,\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: A Message Concerning Elam'
      title: A Message Concerning Elam
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CAnd Hazor will become as a lair of jackals, a waste forever;
        no one will live there, and no son of humankind will dwell as an alien in
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The word of Yahweh that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning Elam
        at the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah the king of Judah, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThus says Yahweh of hosts: \u2018Look, I am going to break
        the bow of Elam, the first and best of their might. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And I will bring to Elam four winds, from the four corners of heaven,
        and I will scatter them to all these winds, and there will not be a nation
        where the scattered people of Elam will not go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So I will shatter Elam before their enemies, and before the seekers
        of their life. And I will bring disaster upon them, my burning anger,\u2019
        declares Yahweh. \u2018And I will send after them the sword until I have
        destroyed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And I will set my throne in Elam and I will destroy from there king
        and officials,\u2019 declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u2018And then in the last of the days I will restore the fortunes
        of Elam,\u2019 declares Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message Concerning Babylon'
      title: A Message Concerning Babylon
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that Yahweh spoke concerning Babylon, concerning the land
        of the Chaldeans, by the hand of Jeremiah the prophet: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDeclare among the nations and proclaim, and lift up a banner.
        Proclaim, you must not conceal it. Say, \u2018Babylon is captured, Bel is
        ashamed, Merodach is filled with terror, her idols are ashamed, her idols
        are filled with terror. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For a nation will come up against her from the north. It will make
        her land as a horror, and an inhabitant will not be in her. From humans to
        animals they all will wander off. They will go away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "In those days and in that time,\u2019&nbsp;\u201D declares Yahweh,
        \u201Cthe people of Israel will come, they and the people of Judah together.
        Weeping as they go, they will go, and Yahweh their God they will seek. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They will ask the way to Zion, turning their faces there. They will
        come and join themselves to Yahweh by an everlasting covenant that will not
        be forgotten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'My people have become lost sheep, their shepherds have caused them
        to go astray. They led them away to the mountains. From mountain to hill
        they have gone, they have forgotten their resting place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All those who found them have devoured them. And their foes have
        said, \u2018We are not guilty, because they have sinned against Yahweh, the
        true pasture,  even Yahweh, the hope of their ancestors.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Flee from the midst of Babylon, and from the land of the Chaldeans.
        Go out and be like he-goats before the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For look, I am going to stir up, and I am going to bring against
        Babylon a contingent of great nations from the land of the north. And they
        will draw up a battle formation against her, from there she will be captured.
        Their arrows are like a warrior who has achieved success, he does not return
        without success. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Chaldea will be as booty, all those who plunder her will be satisfied,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CThough you rejoice, though you exult, O plunderers of my inheritance,
        though you frisk about like a heifer on the grass, and you neigh like the
        powerful stallions, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'your mother will be very ashamed. She who gave birth to you will
        be humiliated.  Look, she will be the least of the nations, a desert, dry
        land, and wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Because of the anger of Yahweh she will not be inhabited, but she
        will be a wasteland, all of her. Everyone who passes by Babylon will be appalled
        and will hiss because of all her wounds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Draw up a battle formation at Babylon all around, all those who bend
        the bow, shoot at her. You must not spare arrows,  for she has sinned against
        Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Raise a war cry against her on all sides. She has surrendered.  Her
        towers have fallen, her walls are ruined. For this is the vengeance of Yahweh.
        Take revenge on her. As she has done to others, so do to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Cut off the sower from Babylon, and the one who uses the sickle in
        the time of harvest. Because of the sword of the oppressor each one will
        turn to their people, and each one will flee to their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Israel is a sheep scattered, lions drove them away. The first who
        devoured it was the king of Assyria, and now at the end Nebuchadnezzar, the
        king of Babylon, gnawed its bones.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CLook,
        I am going to punish the king of Babylon and his land just as I punished
        the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will restore Israel to its pasture, and it will feed on Carmel,
        and in Bashan, and on the hills of Ephraim, and in Gilead its hunger will
        be satisfied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In those days and at that time,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cthe
        guilt of Israel will be sought, but there is none, and the sins of Judah,
        but they will not be found, for I will forgive those I left behind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "To the land of Merathaim, go up against her, and against the inhabitants
        of Pekod, massacre and destroy them,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand do
        according to all that I have commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sound of battle is in the land, and great destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "How the blacksmith\u2019s hammer of all the earth is cut down and
        broken! How Babylon has become as a horror among the nations! "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I laid a bird snare for you, and you were caught, O Babylon. But
        you yourself did not know. You were discovered and seized, because with Yahweh
        you measured yourself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Yahweh has opened his armory, and he has brought out the weapons
        of his wrath, for it is a word for my Lord Yahweh of hosts in the land of
        the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Come against her from the end, open her granaries. Pile her up like
        heaps and destroy her. Let there be no remnant for her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Massacre all her bulls, let them go down to the slaughtering. Woe
        to them, for their day has come, the time of their punishment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'There is the sound of fugitives and survivors from the land of Babylon,
        to declare in Zion the vengeance of Yahweh our God, the vengeance for his
        temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Summon archers against Babylon, all those who bend the bow. Encamp
        all around her, there must not be for her an escape. Take revenge on her
        according to her deeds. According to all that she has done, so do to her.
        For against Yahweh she has behaved insolently, against the Holy One of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore her young men will fall in her public squares, and all
        her soldiers will perish on that day,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CLook, I am against you, O arrogant one,\u201D declares Lord
        Yahweh of hosts, \u201Cfor your day has come, the time when I will punish
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the arrogant one will stumble and fall, and there is no one who
        raises him up. And I will kindle a fire in his cities, and it will devour
        everything around him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CThe people of Israel are oppressed,
        and the people of Judah likewise, for all their captors have seized them,
        they refuse to let them go free. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Their redeemer is strong, his name is Yahweh of hosts. Surely he
        will plead their case, in order to make peace for the earth, but to cause
        unrest to the inhabitants of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "A sword against the Chaldeans,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand against
        the inhabitants of Babylon, and against her officials, and against her wise
        men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'A sword against the oracle priests, and they will become foolish.
        A sword against her warriors, and they will be filled with terror. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'A sword against his horses, and against his chariots,  and against
        all the foreign troops who are in the midst of her, so that they may become
        as women. A sword against her treasures, so that they may be plundered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'A drought will come against her waters, and they will dry up, for
        it is a land of images, and because of the frightful objects, they act like
        madmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Therefore desert creatures will live there with jackals, and daughters
        of ostriches will inhabit her. And she will not be inhabited again forever, 
        and she will not be dwelt in for all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "As when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah and their neighbors,\u201D
        declares Yahweh, \u201Cno one will live there, and the son of humankind will
        not dwell as an alien in her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Look, a people is about to come from the north, and a great nation
        and many kings are woken up from the remotest part of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They keep hold of bow and short sword. They are cruel and they have
        no mercy. Their sound is like the sea, it roars, and upon horses they ride.
        Drawn up for battle as a man for the battle, against you, O daughter of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The king of Babylon heard their report and his hands grew slack.
        Anxiety has seized him, fear and pain like the woman who gives birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Look, like a lion he comes up from the thickets of the Jordan against
        a pastureland by a constantly flowing stream,  so I will chase them away
        quickly from her, and I will appoint whoever is chosen over her. For who
        is like me, and who can summon me, and who is this shepherd who can stand
        before me?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Therefore hear the plan of Yahweh that he has planned against Babylon,
        and his plans that he has planned against the land of the Chaldeans. Surely
        they will drag them away, the little ones of the flock. Surely he will cause
        their grazing place to be desolate over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "At the sound, \u2018Babylon has been captured,\u2019 the earth will
        quake, and a cry for help among the nations will be heard.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " Thus says Yahweh: \u201CLook, I am going to stir up against Babylon
        and against the inhabitants of Leb-qamai a destructive wind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And I will send winnowers to Babylon, and they will winnow her, and
        they will lay waste her land, for they will be against her from all sides
        on the day of disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let not him who bends the bow shoot his bow, and let him not rise
        high in his body armor. And you must not spare her young men; destroy her
        whole army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they will fall slain in the land of the Chaldeans, and pierced
        through in her streets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For neither Israel nor Judah is a widower from their God, from Yahweh
        of hosts, though their land is full of guilt against the Holy One of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Flee from the midst of Babylon and save each one his life. You must
        not perish because of her guilt. For this is the time of vengeance for Yahweh,
        he will repay her what is deserved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Babylon was a cup of gold in the hand of Yahweh, making drunk all
        the earth. The nations drank of her wine. Therefore the nations acted like
        madmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Suddenly Babylon has fallen and she is shattered. Wail over her!
        Take balm for her wounds, perhaps she may be healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We tried to heal Babylon, and she was not healed. Forsake her and
        let us go each one to his country, for her judgment has reached to the heavens,
        and it has been lifted up to the skies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yahweh has brought forth our vindication. Come and let us make known
        in Zion the work of Yahweh our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Sharpen the arrows, fill the quivers! Yahweh has stirred up the spirit
        of the kings of the Medes. Because his plan concerning Babylon is to destroy
        it, for that is the vengeance of Yahweh, the vengeance for his temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Against the walls of Babylon raise a banner; post a strong watch,
        post watchmen, prepare the ambushes, for Yahweh has both planned as well
        as performed what he has spoken concerning the inhabitants of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O you who live by mighty waters, rich in treasures, your end has
        come, the measure of your life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Yahweh of hosts has sworn by himself, \u201CSurely I will fill you
        with troops like the creeping locusts,  and they will sing over you a war
        cry.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He is the one who made the earth by his power, the one who created
        the world by his wisdom, and by his understanding he stretched out the heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At the giving of his voice there is a roar of waters in the heavens,
        and he causes the patches of mist to go up from the end of the earth. He
        makes lightning for the rain, and he brings out the wind from his storehouses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All humankind turns out to be stupid, without knowledge. Every goldsmith
        is put to shame by the divine image. For his cast image is a lie, and there
        is no breath in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They are worthless, a work of mockery. At the time of their punishment,
        they will perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The portion of Jacob is not like these, for he is the creator of
        everything,  and the tribe of his inheritance. Yahweh of hosts is his name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He says, \u201CYou are a war club for me, a weapon of battle, and
        I smash nations with you, and I destroy kingdoms with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And I smash the horse with you, and its rider, and I smash the chariot
        with you, and its rider. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And I smash man and woman with you, and I smash the old man and the
        boy with you, and I smash the young man and the young woman with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And I smash the shepherd and his flock with you, and I smash the
        farmer and his team with you, and I smash the governors and the officials
        with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And I will repay Babylon, and all the inhabitants of Chaldea, all
        their wickedness that they have done in Zion before your eyes,\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CLook, I am against you, O mountain of the destruction,\u201D
        declares Yahweh, \u201Cthe one that destroys the whole earth. And I will
        stretch out my hand against you, and I will roll you down from the cliffs,
        and I will make you as a mountain burned away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They will not take from you a stone for a corner, and a stone for
        a foundation, for you will be an everlasting desolation,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Raise a banner in the land; blow a horn among the nations; prepare
        for holy war against her; summon the nations against her, the kingdoms of
        Ararat, Minni, and Ashkenaz; summon against her an official; bring up horses
        like bristling creeping locusts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Prepare the nations for holy war against her, the kings of the Medes,
        with their governors and all their officials, and every land of their dominion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the land quakes and writhes, for the plans of Yahweh against
        Babylon stand, to make the land of Babylon as a horror, without inhabitant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The warriors of Babylon have ceased to fight, they remain in the
        strongholds, their power has dried up, they have become as women. Her dwelling
        places are set on fire, her bars are broken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'one runner runs to meet another runner, and one messenger to meet
        another messenger, to tell the king of Babylon that his city has been captured,
        from end to end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the fords have been seized, and the reed marshes have been burned
        with fire, and the soldiers are horrified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "For thus says Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, \u201CThe daughter
        of Babylon is like a threshing floor at the time it is trodden down, just
        a little while  and the time of the harvest will come for her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon has devoured me and sucked me
        dry; he has made me an empty vessel; he has swallowed me like the sea monster;
        he has filled his belly with my delicacies; he has rinsed me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CMay the violence done to me and to my flesh be on Babylon,\u201D
        the inhabitants of Zion will say; and \u201CMy blood be upon the inhabitants
        of Chaldea,\u201D Jerusalem will say. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh, \u201CLook, I am going to contend your
        case, and I will avenge your vengeance, and I will cause her sea to dry up,
        and I will cause her fountain to dry up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And Babylon will become as a heap of stones, a lair of jackals, an
        object of horror, and an object of hissing, without inhabitants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They will roar together like the young lions, they will growl like
        the cubs of lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "At their becoming hot I will set their banquets, and I will make
        them drunk, so that they will fall into a swoon, and they will sleep an everlasting
        sleep,  and they will not wake up,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CI will bring them down like young rams to slaughter, like rams
        and goats. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'How Sheshach is captured, and the glory of all the earth is seized!
        How Babylon has become as an object of horror among the nations! '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sea has risen over Babylon, she has been covered by the roar
        of its waves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Her cities have become as an object of horror, a dry land and a wilderness, 
        a land in which no person lives, nor does a son of humankind pass through
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "And I will punish Bel in Babylon, and I will wrench out from his
        mouth what he has swallowed.  And the nations will not stream towards him
        any longer what\u2019s worse, the wall of Babylon has fallen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Come out from her midst, my people, and save each one his life from
        the burning anger of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Now so that you are not fainthearted,  and you are afraid at the
        rumors that are heard in the land\u2014 and in the year the rumor comes,
        and in the year after it the rumor, and violence is in the land, with ruler
        against ruler\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'therefore look, days are coming, and I will punish the images of
        Babylon, and all her land will be put to shame, and all her slain ones will
        fall in the midst of her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then the heaven and the earth and all that is in them will shout
        for joy over Babylon, for from the north the destroyers will come to it,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Babylon must fall not only because of the slain ones of Israel, but
        also because of Babylon the slain ones of all the earth have fallen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Survivors of the sword, go! You must not linger! Remember Yahweh
        from far away, and let Jerusalem come to your mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'We are ashamed, for we have heard taunts,  disgrace covers our faces,
        for strangers have come to the holy places of the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "\u201CTherefore look, days are coming,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        I will punish her images, and the fatally wounded will sigh through all her
        land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Though Babylon goes up to the heavens, and though she fortifies the
        high place of her strength, from me destroyers will come to her,\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The sound of a cry for help from Babylon, and a great collapse from
        the land of the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'For Yahweh is devastating Babylon, and he obliterates her loud noise
        from her. Their waves roar like mighty waters, the roar of their voices resounds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'For a destroyer is coming against her, against Babylon, and her warriors
        are captured. Their bows are broken; for Yahweh is a God of recompense, certainly
        he will repay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "\u201CAnd I will make drunk her officials, and her wise men, her
        governors, and her officials, and her warriors, and they will sleep an everlasting
        sleep,  and they will not wake up,\u201D declares the King, Yahweh of hosts
        is his name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: The Scroll Concerning Babylon is Thrown into the Euphrates'
      title: The Scroll Concerning Babylon is Thrown into the Euphrates
      number: 58
      content: "Thus says Yahweh of hosts: \u201CThe broad walls of Babylon will
        be utterly demolished, and her high gates will burn with fire, and the peoples
        will labor for nothing,  and the nations for fire,  and they will grow weary.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'The word that Jeremiah the prophet commanded Seraiah, the son of
        Neriah, the son of Mahseiah, at his going with Zedekiah, the king of Judah,
        to Babylon in the fourth year of his reign. Now Seraiah was the quartermaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'And Jeremiah wrote all the disasters that would come on Babylon in
        one scroll, all these words that are written concerning Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "And Jeremiah said to Seraiah, \u201CAt your coming to Babylon, then
        you must see that you read aloud all these words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "And you must say, \u2018Yahweh, you yourself spoke against this place,
        to destroy it, so that there will not be in it anything living, from humankind
        to animals, for it will be an everlasting desolation.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And then when you finish reading aloud this scroll, you must tie
        a stone on it, and you must throw it into the middle of the Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "And you must say, \u2018Babylon will sink, and she will not rise,
        because of the face of the disasters that I am bringing on her, and they
        will grow weary.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D Thus far the words of Jeremiah. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'Zedekiah was twenty-one years old at his beginning to reign, and
        he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. And the name of his mother was Hamutal,
        the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did evil in the eyes of Yahweh like all that Jehoiakim had
        done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For because of the anger of Yahweh this happened in Jerusalem and
        Judah until his casting them from his presence. And Zedekiah rebelled against
        the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And then in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth month, on the
        tenth day of the month, Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon came against Jerusalem,
        he and all his army. And they laid siege to it, and built siege works against
        it all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the city came under siege until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In the fourth month, on the ninth day of the month, the famine in
        the city became severe and there was no food for the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the city was breached, and all the soldiers fled and went out
        from the city by night by the way of the gate between the two walls that
        are at the garden of the king, though the Chaldeans were all around the city.
        And they went in the direction of the Jordan Valley.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued after the king and they overtook
        Zedekiah in the plains of Jericho, and all his army was scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then they captured the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon
        at Riblah in the land of Hamath, and he passed sentence on him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the king of Babylon slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his
        eyes, and he also slaughtered all the officials of Judah at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then he made blind the eyes of Zedekiah, and they tied him up with
        bronze fetters, and the king of Babylon brought him to Babylon. And he put
        him in prison until the day of his death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now in the fifth month, on the tenth day of the month, which was
        the nineteenth year of King Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, Nebuzaradan
        the captain of the guard, who stood before the king of Babylon, entered into
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he burned the temple of Yahweh, and the palace of the king, and
        all the houses of Jerusalem, even every great house he burned with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And all the army of the Chaldeans who were with the captain of the
        guard broke down all the walls of Jerusalem all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard deported some of the poor
        of the people, and the rest of the people who were left in the city, and
        the deserters who deserted to the king of Babylon, along with the rest of
        the craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard left some of the poor of
        the land to serve as vinedressers and farmers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the Chaldeans broke the pillars of bronze that were in the temple
        of Yahweh, and the kettle stands and the sea of bronze that were in the temple
        of Yahweh, and they carried all their bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they took with them the pots, and the shovels, and the snuffers,
        and the sprinkling bowls, and the pans, and all the vessels of bronze which
        were used in temple service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the captain of the guard took the bowls, and the firepans, and
        the sprinkling bowls, and the pots, and the lampstands, and the pans, and
        the libation bowls, those made of solid gold and those made of solid silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The two pillars, the one sea, and the twelve bronze oxen that were
        under the kettle stands which King Solomon had made for the temple of Yahweh\u2014there
        was not a weight for the bronze of all these vessels! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the pillars, the height of one pillar was eighteen cubits, and
        a thread of twelve cubits surrounded it, and its thickness was four fingers,
        hollowed out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And a capital upon it was bronze and the height of the one capital
        was five cubits, and latticework and pomegranates were on the capital on
        all sides, all of bronze. And like these was the second pillar with pomegranates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And there were ninety-six pomegranates on the sides; all the pomegranates
        on the latticework on all sides were a hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest, and
        Zephaniah the second priest, and three keepers of the threshold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And from the city he took one high official who was chief officer
        over the soldiers, and seven men of the king\u2019s advisors who were found
        in the city, and the secretary of the commander of the army who levied for
        military service the people of the land, and sixty men of the people of the
        land who were found in the midst of the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them and brought them
        to the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the king of Babylon struck them down and killed them at Riblah
        in the land of Hamath. So Judah left from its land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the number of the people whom Nebuchadnezzar deported: in
        the seventh year, three thousand twenty-three Judeans; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar, eight hundred and thirty-two
        persons from Jerusalem; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: An Allowance for Jehoiachin'
      title: An Allowance for Jehoiachin
      number: 30
      content: 'in the twenty-third year of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuzaradan, the captain
        of the guard, deported seven hundred and forty-five Judean persons; there
        were four thousand six hundred persons in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And then in the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin, the
        king of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-fifth day of the month,
        Evil-merodach, the king of Babylon, in the first year of his reign, lifted
        up the head of Jehoiachin, the king of Judah, and brought him out from prison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then he spoke with him kindly and gave his seat above the seats of
        the kings who were with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So he changed the garments of his imprisonment and he ate food before
        him continually all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And his allowance, a continual allowance was given to him by the
        king of Babylon on a daily basis all the days of his life up to the day of
        his death. '
      comments: []
